ls to determine the most qualified bidders and award the job to one or more freelancers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Payments<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Each registered user is provided with a free online account for payments or fund transfers. Funds can be added as direct payments from other users through contracts or from various payment sources such as the user&rsquo;s credit card, online payment accounts or bank transfer.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Buyers can pay service providers via transfer from their accounts to providers&rsquo; accounts.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>A freelancer may withdraw funds from his or her iJobDesk.com account via various Payment Methods such as Paypal, Bank and so on. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Fees payable to iJobDesk.com are also deducted from users&rsquo; accounts as applied.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Feedback and Ratings<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>When a contract is completed through payments made within the iJobDesk.com system, the feedback and rating system for the contract will be activated. This provides the opportunity for the buyer and the freelancer to rate each other&rsquo;s performance through comments and a simple 5-star rating scale. A freelancer&rsquo;s overall ratings and individual contract ratings and feedback are shown on the freelancer&rsquo;s profile page to help buyers assess the value of working with the freelancer.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 'what-is-ijobdesk', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 14:43:32', '2018-06-08 03:43:24', NULL),
	(24, '{"en":"Getting Started as a Buyer","ch":"Getting Started as a Buyer"}', '{"en":"<p>Getting started on iJobDesk is simple, and the easiest way to get the job done is to understand three phases: before hiring, hiring, and doing work.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Before hiring<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/signup\\/buyer\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Sign up<\\/a> link on iJobDesk.com home page. On the sign up page, provide your name, email address, username and password. Read our <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/privacy-policy\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Privacy Policy<\\/a>. Create an account by submitting and then confirm your email address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/payment-methods\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Add your payment method<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/deposit\\" target=\\"_blank\\">deposit funds<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/job\\/post\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Post a job<\\/a> (you may post an hourly job or a fixed-price job)<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Hiring<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Evaluate the applications and shortlist those as you like.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You may also find qualified freelancers and invite them to the job you posted.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Interview your best applicants, and send an offer to hire the best.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Doing work<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Have a kick-off meeting to establish ground rules on availability, timeline, communication, expectations, deliverables, etc.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Manage your project. Communicate with your freelancer regularly. Review work in progress regularly using the Work Diary for an hourly job, project milestone deliverables, and other reports.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure that you have funds enough to make payments for hourly contracts. You cannot use Escrow Payment System for your hourly contracts. But you can use Escrow Payment System for your fixed-price contracts. You may fund in Escrow for milestones of a fixed-price contract before you start the contract. You will release funds in Escrow when you are 100% satisfied with the deliverables for a milestone of the fixed-price contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You are now ready to be a Buyer at iJobDesk.com!<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Getting started on iJobDesk is simple, and the easiest way to get the job done is to understand three phases: before hiring, hiring, and doing work.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Before hiring<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/signup\\/buyer\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Sign up<\\/a> link on iJobDesk.com home page. On the sign up page, provide your name, email address, username and password. Read our <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/privacy-policy\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Privacy Policy<\\/a>. Create an account by submitting and then confirm your email address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/payment-methods\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Add your payment method<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/deposit\\" target=\\"_blank\\">deposit funds<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/job\\/post\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Post a job<\\/a> (you may post an hourly job or a fixed-price job)<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Hiring<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Evaluate the applications and shortlist those as you like.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You may also find qualified freelancers and invite them to the job you posted.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Interview your best applicants, and send an offer to hire the best.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Doing work<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Have a kick-off meeting to establish ground rules on availability, timeline, communication, expectations, deliverables, etc.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Manage your project. Communicate with your freelancer regularly. Review work in progress regularly using the Work Diary for an hourly job, project milestone deliverables, and other reports.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure that you have funds enough to make payments for hourly contracts. You cannot use Escrow Payment System for your hourly contracts. But you can use Escrow Payment System for your fixed-price contracts. You may fund in Escrow for milestones of a fixed-price contract before you start the contract. You will release funds in Escrow when you are 100% satisfied with the deliverables for a milestone of the fixed-price contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You are now ready to be a Buyer at iJobDesk.com!<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 1, NULL, 'getting-started-as-a-buyer', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 14:44:21', '2018-06-07 14:44:21', NULL),
	(25, '{"en":"Can I be both a Freelancer doing work and a Buyer hiring on iJobDesk?","ch":"Can I be both a Freelancer doing work and a Buyer hiring on iJobDesk?"}', '{"en":"<p>No, you cannot be both a freelancer and a client at the same time on iJobDesk.com.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to choose whether you work as a freelancer or hire as a buyer when you sign up.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>No, you cannot be both a freelancer and a client at the same time on iJobDesk.com.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to choose whether you work as a freelancer or hire as a buyer when you sign up.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 2, NULL, 'can-i-be-both-a-freelancer-doing-work-and-a-buyer-hiring-on-ijobdesk', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 14:46:24', '2018-06-07 14:46:24', NULL),
	(26, '{"en":"Hourly vs. Fixed-Price Contract Differences","ch":"Hourly vs. Fixed-Price Contract Differences"}', '{"en":"<h4>If you are a Buyer:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Sending an Offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Negotiate an hourly billing rate when you interview the Freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Negotiate a cost for the full project or create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Project Management:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Your freelancers need to have the iJobDesk Desktop App installed and running to qualify their work. You can review their Work Diary regularly.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Funds are deposited into iJobDesk Escrow. You will review the deliverables for a milestone and release payment for the milestone when you are 100% satisfied.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment Protection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: No payment protection. Your Freelancers will be notified when you have no funds enough to make payment in your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You will be billed on a weekly basis.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: You deposit funds for milestones into iJobDesk Escrow and release at the completion of a milestone or project.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>If you are a Freelancer:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Receiving an Offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Negotiate an hourly billing rate when you interview the Buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Negotiate a cost for the full project or create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Working on a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You need to have the iJobDesk Desktop App installed and running to qualify your work. You can review your Work Diary regularly and delete screenshots unrelated to the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: You complete and submit specified milestone deliverables to the Buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment Protection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: No payment protection. You will be notified when the Buyer has no funds enough to make payment.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You will get paid on a weekly basis. Funds will be available in your account after a review and security hold period.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Funds will be submitted to iJobDesk Escrow and released at the completion of a milestone or project.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<h4>If you are a Buyer:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Sending an Offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Negotiate an hourly billing rate when you interview the Freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Negotiate a cost for the full project or create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Project Management:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Your freelancers need to have the iJobDesk Desktop App installed and running to qualify their work. You can review their Work Diary regularly.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Funds are deposited into iJobDesk Escrow. You will review the deliverables for a milestone and release payment for the milestone when you are 100% satisfied.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment Protection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: No payment protection. Your Freelancers will be notified when you have no funds enough to make payment in your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You will be billed on a weekly basis.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: You deposit funds for milestones into iJobDesk Escrow and release at the completion of a milestone or project.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>If you are a Freelancer:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Receiving an Offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: Negotiate an hourly billing rate when you interview the Buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Negotiate a cost for the full project or create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Working on a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You need to have the iJobDesk Desktop App installed and running to qualify your work. You can review your Work Diary regularly and delete screenshots unrelated to the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: You complete and submit specified milestone deliverables to the Buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment Protection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: No payment protection. You will be notified when the Buyer has no funds enough to make payment.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Payment<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly Contract: You will get paid on a weekly basis. Funds will be available in your account after a review and security hold period.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-Price Contract: Funds will be submitted to iJobDesk Escrow and released at the completion of a milestone or project.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 1, 0, 3, NULL, 'hourly-vs-fixed-price-contract-differences', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 14:47:50', '2018-06-07 14:47:50', NULL),
	(27, '{"en":"What is a Featured Job?","ch":"What is a Featured Job?"}', '{"en":"<p>It means that a motivated Buyer has paid to upgrade their job post in order to help it stand out on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><img src=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/assets\\/images\\/common\\/featured.png\\" alt=\\"featured\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A featured job will be clearly marked in the job feed with the ribbon above.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Buyer has paid to have their job highlighted in the job feed to reach more freelancers.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>It means that a motivated Buyer has paid to upgrade their job post in order to help it stand out on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><img src=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/assets\\/images\\/common\\/featured.png\\" alt=\\"featured\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A featured job will be clearly marked in the job feed with the ribbon above.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Buyer has paid to have their job highlighted in the job feed to reach more freelancers.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 4, NULL, 'what-is-a-featured-job', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 14:49:09', '2018-06-07 14:49:09', NULL),
	(28, '{"en":"What is a Freelancer\'s Job Success Score?","ch":"What is a Freelancer\'s Job Success Score?"}', '{"en":"<p>A Job Success Score reflects their reputation on iJobDesk based on Buyer feedback and other indicators of buyer satisfaction. It combines metrics on their buyers&rsquo; feedback, long-term relationships with buyers, buyer rehires, and incompletion of work in contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A freelancer with scores of 90 % and above have consistently delighted their buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A freelancer with a score in the 80s has done solid work but also their buyers see some room for improvement.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Scores of 79% and below may indicate that the freelancer has been struggling to meet their buyers&rsquo; expectations.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>A Job Success Score reflects their reputation on iJobDesk based on Buyer feedback and other indicators of buyer satisfaction. It combines metrics on their buyers&rsquo; feedback, long-term relationships with buyers, buyer rehires, and incompletion of work in contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A freelancer with scores of 90 % and above have consistently delighted their buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A freelancer with a score in the 80s has done solid work but also their buyers see some room for improvement.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Scores of 79% and below may indicate that the freelancer has been struggling to meet their buyers&rsquo; expectations.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 5, NULL, 'what-is-a-freelancers-job-success-score', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 14:50:13', '2018-06-08 03:47:07', NULL),
	(29, '{"en":"Why Shouldn\'t I Pay or Get Paid Directly?","ch":"Why Shouldn\'t I Pay or Get Paid Directly?"}', '{"en":"<p>iJobDesk requires all payments to go through our platform.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can be assured that payments made through iJobDesk are safe, timely, and hassle-free.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In an hourly contract, buyers should only pay for hours worked and freelancers should be paid for their time spent working. In a fixed-price contract, iJobDesk Escrow helps ensure buyers get the work done and freelancers get paid for work completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case a buyer or freelancer suggests that you accept a payment or pay them outside of iJobDesk, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">report it<\\/a> to us immediately. We will investigate and take action as appropriate. Sending or receiving payment directly is a violation of iJobDesk&rsquo;s Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>iJobDesk requires all payments to go through our platform.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can be assured that payments made through iJobDesk are safe, timely, and hassle-free.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In an hourly contract, buyers should only pay for hours worked and freelancers should be paid for their time spent working. In a fixed-price contract, iJobDesk Escrow helps ensure buyers get the work done and freelancers get paid for work completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case a buyer or freelancer suggests that you accept a payment or pay them outside of iJobDesk, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">report it<\\/a> to us immediately. We will investigate and take action as appropriate. Sending or receiving payment directly is a violation of iJobDesk&rsquo;s Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 6, NULL, 'why-shouldnt-i-pay-or-get-paid-directly', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:04:44', '2018-06-07 15:04:44', NULL),
	(30, '{"en":"Violations and Account Holds","ch":"Violations and Account Holds"}', '{"en":"<p>You are expected to comply with all iJobDesk <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and the failure to do so can result in account holds. Account holds lead to account interruptions, and consequences could include the inability to continue working on iJobDesk and the loss of your hard-earned reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here are the most common violations:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Identity uncertainty and Account sharing: Provide your own accurate information and use a clear photo of yourself. Do not allow anyone else to use your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Payments off iJobDesk: Always make payment or receive payment through iJobDesk. In case a buyer proposes to pay you outside of iJobDesk or a freelancer asks you to pay outside of iJobDesk, decline and let us know.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Failing to perform on your contracts: When you accept a contract, you promise to complete the work and to deliver high-quality work on time. And you have to describe your business, skills ,and services you offer. In case you misrepresent them, it can result in low buyer satisfaction and payment disputes.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Contact information sharing: You keep contact information with potential buyers inside iJobDesk. In your freelancer profile, do not include your email, Skype ID, or links to any sites (such as your personal website, a third-party profile, etc.) that include a way to contact you outside of iJobDesk.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Account holds for any of these reasons will be counted and disqualify you from getting the high reputation.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You are expected to comply with all iJobDesk <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and the failure to do so can result in account holds. Account holds lead to account interruptions, and consequences could include the inability to continue working on iJobDesk and the loss of your hard-earned reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here are the most common violations:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Identity uncertainty and Account sharing: Provide your own accurate information and use a clear photo of yourself. Do not allow anyone else to use your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Payments off iJobDesk: Always make payment or receive payment through iJobDesk. In case a buyer proposes to pay you outside of iJobDesk or a freelancer asks you to pay outside of iJobDesk, decline and let us know.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Failing to perform on your contracts: When you accept a contract, you promise to complete the work and to deliver high-quality work on time. And you have to describe your business, skills ,and services you offer. In case you misrepresent them, it can result in low buyer satisfaction and payment disputes.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Contact information sharing: You keep contact information with potential buyers inside iJobDesk. In your freelancer profile, do not include your email, Skype ID, or links to any sites (such as your personal website, a third-party profile, etc.) that include a way to contact you outside of iJobDesk.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Account holds for any of these reasons will be counted and disqualify you from getting the high reputation.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 7, NULL, 'violations-and-account-holds', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:05:16', '2018-06-08 03:49:22', NULL),
	(31, '{"en":"Report Suspicious User Activity","ch":"Report Suspicious User Activity"}', '{"en":"<h4>Report Job<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you find a job or invitation that looks suspicious or inappropriate, please get in touch with us as soon as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We will investigate and take the appropriate measures. We will not share your identity with the user you reported.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Profile<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Please report any profile you see that contains violations of our identity policy, such as fake names, fake portraits, and duplicate accounts. We will review the profile and take action as appropriate. We will not share your identity with the user you reported.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Buyer<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you ever come across inappropriate buyer behavior, please save evidence of your experience and get in touch with us as soon as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Please get in touch with us in the following cases:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer asks you to pay money to get a job.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer requests you contact them directly via email, chat, or other means before they invite you to interview or hire you on a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer requests for your contact information, such as your email address, or phone number before they invite you to interview or hire you on a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer offers to pay you directly via PayPal, or other methods outside of the iJobDesk finance system.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer asks you to start working before they hire you for an official iJobDesk job contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Other cases may require you to contact us.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Freelancer<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you believe a freelancer has violated iJobDesk Terms and Conditions, please contact Customer Support by clicking <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to report the inappropriate behavior. When you contact Customer Support, please provide a clear proof you have such as chat history, email messages, files, etc.<\\/p>","ch":"<h4>Report Job<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you find a job or invitation that looks suspicious or inappropriate, please get in touch with us as soon as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We will investigate and take the appropriate measures. We will not share your identity with the user you reported.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Profile<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Please report any profile you see that contains violations of our identity policy, such as fake names, fake portraits, and duplicate accounts. We will review the profile and take action as appropriate. We will not share your identity with the user you reported.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Buyer<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you ever come across inappropriate buyer behavior, please save evidence of your experience and get in touch with us as soon as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Please get in touch with us in the following cases:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer asks you to pay money to get a job.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer requests you contact them directly via email, chat, or other means before they invite you to interview or hire you on a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer requests for your contact information, such as your email address, or phone number before they invite you to interview or hire you on a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer offers to pay you directly via PayPal, or other methods outside of the iJobDesk finance system.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A buyer asks you to start working before they hire you for an official iJobDesk job contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Other cases may require you to contact us.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Report Freelancer<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>If you believe a freelancer has violated iJobDesk Terms and Conditions, please contact Customer Support by clicking <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to report the inappropriate behavior. When you contact Customer Support, please provide a clear proof you have such as chat history, email messages, files, etc.<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 8, NULL, 'report-suspicious-user-activity', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:05:49', '2018-06-07 15:05:49', NULL),
