	(33, '{"en":"What browsers does iJobDesk support?","ch":"What browsers does iJobDesk support?"}', '{"en":"<p>iJobDesk officially supports the current version of the following browsers:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Google Chrome<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Mozilla Firefox<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Microsoft Edge<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Apple Safari<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>iJobDesk officially supports the current version of the following browsers:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Google Chrome<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Mozilla Firefox<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Microsoft Edge<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Apple Safari<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 1, 0, 10, NULL, 'what-browsers-does-ijobdesk-support', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:08:15', '2018-06-07 15:08:15', NULL),
	(34, '{"en":"Affiliate Program","ch":"Affiliate Program"}', '{"en":"<p>There is more than one way to earn through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The iJobDesk Affiliate Program allows you to receive payments from iJobDesk into your account for referring a buyer or a freelancer through referral links you can see <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/affiliate\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To view the affiliate payments:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>Go to Accounts Menu &gt; Affiliate Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>How does it work?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Affiliate Program will send invitation messages to your friends or colleagues that contain simple guide including your referral link. They sign up through the referral link as Buyer or Freelancer. The referral link is unique and it contains your username to identify your referrals. You&rsquo;ve done it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will get paid on a monthly basis.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><p>Invite a Buyer and earn $50 (USD)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>A buyer that has been registered through your referral link will post jobs and hire Freelancers on iJobDesk. When the buyer deposits funds into their iJobDesk account, you will earn $50 USD.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><p>Invite a Freelancer and earn 1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning. <\\/p> \\r\\n\\t\\t<p>A freelancer that has been registered through your referral link will start working on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>You will then receive 1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning from iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In case a User you invited invites a freelancer, you will earn 0.1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>There is more than one way to earn through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The iJobDesk Affiliate Program allows you to receive payments from iJobDesk into your account for referring a buyer or a freelancer through referral links you can see <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/affiliate\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To view the affiliate payments:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>Go to Accounts Menu &gt; Affiliate Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>How does it work?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Affiliate Program will send invitation messages to your friends or colleagues that contain simple guide including your referral link. They sign up through the referral link as Buyer or Freelancer. The referral link is unique and it contains your username to identify your referrals. You&rsquo;ve done it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will get paid on a monthly basis.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><p>Invite a Buyer and earn $50 (USD)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>A buyer that has been registered through your referral link will post jobs and hire Freelancers on iJobDesk. When the buyer deposits funds into their iJobDesk account, you will earn $50 USD.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><p>Invite a Freelancer and earn 1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning. <\\/p> \\r\\n\\t\\t<p>A freelancer that has been registered through your referral link will start working on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>You will then receive 1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning from iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In case a User you invited invites a freelancer, you will earn 0.1% of the freelancer&rsquo;s earning.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 1, 0, 11, NULL, 'affiliate-program', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:08:46', '2018-06-12 13:50:18', NULL),
	(35, '{"en":"Manage My Email Notifications","ch":"Manage My Email Notifications"}', '{"en":"<p>You can opt out of receiving emails about many actions on iJobDesk. You can opt back in anytime.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To change your email notification settings:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Notification Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>By default, you will receive all email notifications. Clear any checkbox with a notification you don\\u2019t want to receive by email.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Save your changes.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Some notifications are required and you cannot opt out.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can opt out of receiving emails about many actions on iJobDesk. You can opt back in anytime.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To change your email notification settings:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Notification Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>By default, you will receive all email notifications. Clear any checkbox with a notification you don\\u2019t want to receive by email.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Save your changes.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Some notifications are required and you cannot opt out.<\\/p>"}', 2, 0, 0, NULL, 'manage-my-email-notifications', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:33:05', '2018-06-07 15:33:05', NULL),
	(36, '{"en":"Change Password","ch":"Change Password"}', '{"en":"<p>If you lost a device where you were logged into the iJobDesk app or site (laptop, phone, etc.), please change your password and security question immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change your password:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And then click Change Password.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change security question, please click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/secure-question\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To reset a forgotten password, please click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/forgot\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>If you lost a device where you were logged into the iJobDesk app or site (laptop, phone, etc.), please change your password and security question immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change your password:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And then click Change Password.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change security question, please click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/secure-question\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To reset a forgotten password, please click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/forgot\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a>.<\\/p>"}', 2, 0, 1, NULL, 'change-password', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:33:34', '2018-06-07 15:33:34', NULL),
	(37, '{"en":"Reset Your Password","ch":"Reset Your Password"}', '{"en":"<p>You&rsquo;re about to log in, but you forget what your password is. Here&rsquo;s a simple solution: the Forgot Password feature.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To reset your password:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/forgot\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Forgot Password<\\/a> link on the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/login\\" target=\\"_blank\\">login form<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter your email address. We will then send an email that will allow you to reset your password. Be sure to check your spam, junk, and\\/or trash folders if you can&rsquo;t find the reset email. This email is time sensitive, which the reset link will only work for an hour.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Follow the email&rsquo;s link to set a new password.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You&rsquo;re about to log in, but you forget what your password is. Here&rsquo;s a simple solution: the Forgot Password feature.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To reset your password:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/forgot\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Forgot Password<\\/a> link on the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/login\\" target=\\"_blank\\">login form<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter your email address. We will then send an email that will allow you to reset your password. Be sure to check your spam, junk, and\\/or trash folders if you can&rsquo;t find the reset email. This email is time sensitive, which the reset link will only work for an hour.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Follow the email&rsquo;s link to set a new password.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 2, 0, 2, NULL, 'reset-your-password', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:34:05', '2018-06-07 15:34:05', NULL),
	(38, '{"en":"Change Security Question","ch":"Change Security Question"}', '{"en":"<h4>What is Security Question?<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We want to support safe and believable platform that you can trust and build your own business on it.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To improve your account safety, you have to choose security questions and type answers. You will be asked to answer your security questions when accessing some important pages.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Please note that you cannot access your account when you forget it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to change your security question<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Please follow the steps:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>And then click Change Security Question.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<h4>What is Security Question?<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We want to support safe and believable platform that you can trust and build your own business on it.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To improve your account safety, you have to choose security questions and type answers. You will be asked to answer your security questions when accessing some important pages.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Please note that you cannot access your account when you forget it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to change your security question<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Please follow the steps:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Settings.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>And then click Change Security Question.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 2, 0, 3, NULL, 'change-security-question', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:34:35', '2018-06-07 15:34:35', NULL),
	(39, '{"en":"Close My Account","ch":"Close My Account"}', '{"en":"<p>You must clear any outstanding open, active, or pending activity before you close your account.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Closing your account cannot be undone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For freelancer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you close your freelancer account, you must:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Close all open contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure all payments have been received and withdrawn from iJobDesk<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>And follow the steps to close your freelancer account:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts &gt; Settings &gt; My Account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Close My Account link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Input the required information and click Go button to confirm that you want to close your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For buyer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you close your buyer account, you must:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Close all open contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure all outstanding billing is paid within iJobDesk<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>And follow the steps to close your freelancer account:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts &gt; Settings &gt; My Account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Close My Account link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Input the required information and click Go button to confirm that you want to close your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You must clear any outstanding open, active, or pending activity before you close your account.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Closing your account cannot be undone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For freelancer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you close your freelancer account, you must:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Close all open contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure all payments have been received and withdrawn from iJobDesk<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>And follow the steps to close your freelancer account:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts &gt; Settings &gt; My Account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Close My Account link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Input the required information and click Go button to confirm that you want to close your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For buyer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you close your buyer account, you must:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Close all open contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ensure all outstanding billing is paid within iJobDesk<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>And follow the steps to close your freelancer account:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts &gt; Settings &gt; My Account.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Close My Account link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Input the required information and click Go button to confirm that you want to close your account.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 2, 0, 4, NULL, 'close-my-account', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:35:14', '2018-06-07 15:35:14', NULL),
	(40, '{"en":"Post a Job","ch":"Post a Job"}', '{"en":"<p>When you need work done, please post a job in iJobDesk. Freelancers in iJobDesk can find the job posting, send proposals and you can interview them.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To post a job:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click Post a Job.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will describe the job details and adjust the job settings.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>What is important to post a job?<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Scope<\\/strong> - Please include as many details as possible for potential freelancers to understand what you need to be done exactly.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Project Type<\\/strong> - Do you prefer to pay per hour (hourly jobs) or a set amount for the whole job (fixed-price jobs)? What is your budget?<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Deadline<\\/strong> - When does the work need to be done?<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Funds<\\/strong> - Please deposit funds in your account to start a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>What&rsquo;s the difference between paying hourly vs. fixed-price?<\\/h4>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly contracts: You&rsquo;ll be billed weekly, automatically, based on the verifiable hours your freelancer works. You can set up a limit for your freelancer on hours per week.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-price contracts: You&rsquo;ll pay your freelancer as you receive the work. You may create milestones and make payments for each milestone when you receive deliverables and are 100% satisfied. You will deposit funds in Escrow at the beginning of a milestone or a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>When you need work done, please post a job in iJobDesk. Freelancers in iJobDesk can find the job posting, send proposals and you can interview them.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To post a job:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click Post a Job.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will describe the job details and adjust the job settings.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>What is important to post a job?<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Scope<\\/strong> - Please include as many details as possible for potential freelancers to understand what you need to be done exactly.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Project Type<\\/strong> - Do you prefer to pay per hour (hourly jobs) or a set amount for the whole job (fixed-price jobs)? What is your budget?<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Deadline<\\/strong> - When does the work need to be done?<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>Funds<\\/strong> - Please deposit funds in your account to start a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>What&rsquo;s the difference between paying hourly vs. fixed-price?<\\/h4>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hourly contracts: You&rsquo;ll be billed weekly, automatically, based on the verifiable hours your freelancer works. You can set up a limit for your freelancer on hours per week.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fixed-price contracts: You&rsquo;ll pay your freelancer as you receive the work. You may create milestones and make payments for each milestone when you receive deliverables and are 100% satisfied. You will deposit funds in Escrow at the beginning of a milestone or a contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 6, 0, 0, NULL, 'post-a-job', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:37:04', '2018-06-07 15:38:01', NULL),
	(41, '{"en":"Edit \\/ Close \\/ Cancel a Posted Job","ch":"Edit \\/ Close \\/ Cancel a Posted Job"}', '{"en":"<p>You can edit everything about your job posting.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>To edit a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to edit in opening job list and click Edit in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To close a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to close in opening job list and click Close in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To cancel a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to cancel in opening job list and click Cancel in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can edit everything about your job posting.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>To edit a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to edit in opening job list and click Edit in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To close a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to close in opening job list and click Close in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To cancel a posted job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to cancel in opening job list and click Cancel in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 6, 0, 1, NULL, 'edit-close-cancel-a-posted-job', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:39:07', '2018-06-07 15:39:07', NULL),
	(42, '{"en":"How to stop more freelancers from submitting proposals","ch":"How to stop more freelancers from submitting proposals"}', '{"en":"<p>You can change the visibility or close the job entirely to stop more freelancers from submitting proposals.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In case you don&rsquo;t plan to hire any (or any more) freelancers for your job, please close it. You can repost it later.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To change the visibility of a job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to change in opening job list and click Visibility &gt; Private in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To close a job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to close in opening job list and click Close in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can change the visibility or close the job entirely to stop more freelancers from submitting proposals.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In case you don&rsquo;t plan to hire any (or any more) freelancers for your job, please close it. You can repost it later.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To change the visibility of a job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to change in opening job list and click Visibility &gt; Private in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To close a job:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to close in opening job list and click Close in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 6, 0, 2, NULL, 'how-to-stop-more-freelancers-from-submitting-proposals', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:39:44', '2018-06-07 15:39:44', NULL),
	(43, '{"en":"Repost a job","ch":"Repost a job"}', '{"en":"<p>You can re-post jobs that are canceled or closed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To re-post a job:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And then click View All Job Postings link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to repost in Archived Tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The form will pre-populate all the fields with the previous job&rsquo;s information. Please update details as you need, then click Post Job button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can re-post jobs that are canceled or closed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To re-post a job:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And then click View All Job Postings link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want to repost in Archived Tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The form will pre-populate all the fields with the previous job&rsquo;s information. Please update details as you need, then click Post Job button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 6, 0, 3, NULL, 'repost-a-job', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:40:18', '2018-06-07 15:40:18', NULL),
	(44, '{"en":"My job posting has been removed. What happened?","ch":"My job posting has been removed. What happened?"}', '{"en":"<p>There may be a couple of reasons why we removed your job post. You will receive an email notification why it has been removed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If, for some reason, you didn&rsquo;t receive notification from iJobDesk about your missing job post, here is a possible reason why:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The job posting violated the iJobDesk Terms and Conditions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>There may be a couple of reasons why we removed your job post. You will receive an email notification why it has been removed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If, for some reason, you didn&rsquo;t receive notification from iJobDesk about your missing job post, here is a possible reason why:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The job posting violated the iJobDesk Terms and Conditions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 6, 0, 4, NULL, 'my-job-posting-has-been-removed-what-happened', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:40:54', '2018-06-07 15:40:54', NULL),
	(45, '{"en":"Find Freelancers","ch":"Find Freelancers"}', '{"en":"<p>When you have a job (or a project), you have to find the right freelancer to complete the job successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We provide several ways to filter your search results based on the things such as freelancer&rsquo;s hourly rate, skills, feedback and so on. You can use the filters that are available in the box on the left side.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To search for freelancers and filter:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click Find Freelancers.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>From here, search by keyword or use an empty string for all.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>After your initial search, use the filters to refine your search result further.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>When you have a job (or a project), you have to find the right freelancer to complete the job successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We provide several ways to filter your search results based on the things such as freelancer&rsquo;s hourly rate, skills, feedback and so on. You can use the filters that are available in the box on the left side.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To search for freelancers and filter:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers menu, and click Find Freelancers.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>From here, search by keyword or use an empty string for all.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>After your initial search, use the filters to refine your search result further.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 7, 0, 0, NULL, 'find-freelancers', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:41:29', '2018-06-07 15:41:29', NULL),
	(46, '{"en":"Invite Freelancers to a Job Posting","ch":"Invite Freelancers to a Job Posting"}', '{"en":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve posted a job, you can simply sit back and wait for the proposals to roll in.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Or you may be a little more proactive by searching for talented freelancers directly and inviting them to the job posting.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To invite a freelancer to your job posting:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/search\\/freelancers\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Find a freelancer<\\/a> you like.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Invite to Job button on the freelancer&rsquo;s profile<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fill in the comment box and click submit button to invite the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve posted a job, you can simply sit back and wait for the proposals to roll in.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Or you may be a little more proactive by searching for talented freelancers directly and inviting them to the job posting.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To invite a freelancer to your job posting:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/search\\/freelancers\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Find a freelancer<\\/a> you like.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Invite to Job button on the freelancer&rsquo;s profile<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fill in the comment box and click submit button to invite the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 7, 0, 1, NULL, 'invite-freelancers-to-a-job-posting', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:41:56', '2018-06-07 15:41:56', NULL),
	(47, '{"en":"Save a Freelancer for later","ch":"Save a Freelancer for later"}', '{"en":"<p>Please use the save feature if you find a freelancer you&rsquo;d like to contact at a later date.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To save a freelancer from their profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Perform a search and find a freelancer you like. Click the freelancer profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Save button at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To access your list of saved freelancers:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Freelancers<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose the Saved Freelancers tab<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Please use the save feature if you find a freelancer you&rsquo;d like to contact at a later date.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To save a freelancer from their profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Perform a search and find a freelancer you like. Click the freelancer profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Save button at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To access your list of saved freelancers:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Freelancers<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose the Saved Freelancers tab<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 7, 0, 2, NULL, 'save-a-freelancer-for-later', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:42:26', '2018-06-07 15:42:26', NULL),
	(48, '{"en":"Review proposals","ch":"Review proposals"}', '{"en":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve posted a job, you can simply sit back and wait for the proposals to roll in.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can review proposals carefully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To manage your applicants:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Jobs tab to see the My Jobs list.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>As you review their proposals, you can take one of the following actions:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Start interview by sending a message - Contact the freelancer to discuss their proposal.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Hire a freelancer - Set contract terms and, if accepted, hire the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Decline a proposal - Notify the freelancer you are not interested and why.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Archive a proposal - Hide the proposal from your list without rejecting it.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve posted a job, you can simply sit back and wait for the proposals to roll in.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can review proposals carefully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To manage your applicants:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Jobs tab to see the My Jobs list.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>As you review their proposals, you can take one of the following actions:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Start interview by sending a message - Contact the freelancer to discuss their proposal.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Hire a freelancer - Set contract terms and, if accepted, hire the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Decline a proposal - Notify the freelancer you are not interested and why.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<li>Archive a proposal - Hide the proposal from your list without rejecting it.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 7, 0, 3, NULL, 'review-proposals', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:42:57', '2018-06-07 15:42:57', NULL),
	(49, '{"en":"Interview a Freelancer","ch":"Interview a Freelancer"}', '{"en":"<p>Finding the right freelancer for your job is the key to complete a project successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to interview freelancers before you hire to save you time and money down the road.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can start an interview by sending a message to a freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Jobs and locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Review Proposals and locate the proposal you want to interview.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Send Message button to contact the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once you complete this process, the applicant is moved automatically to your Interviews Tab for further review. From this point, you can continue communicating through iJobDesk Messages. Or you may exchange contact information and take the interview to another medium, such as email, chat, or telephone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to decide if it&rsquo;s the right match for your project. And please negotiate the terms of the contract before hiring a freelancer.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Finding the right freelancer for your job is the key to complete a project successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to interview freelancers before you hire to save you time and money down the road.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can start an interview by sending a message to a freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Jobs and locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Review Proposals and locate the proposal you want to interview.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Send Message button to contact the freelancer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once you complete this process, the applicant is moved automatically to your Interviews Tab for further review. From this point, you can continue communicating through iJobDesk Messages. Or you may exchange contact information and take the interview to another medium, such as email, chat, or telephone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to decide if it&rsquo;s the right match for your project. And please negotiate the terms of the contract before hiring a freelancer.<\\/p>"}', 7, 0, 4, NULL, 'interview-a-freelancer', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:43:22', '2018-06-07 15:43:22', NULL),
	(50, '{"en":"Make an Offer to Hire a Freelancer","ch":"Make an Offer to Hire a Freelancer"}', '{"en":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve reviewed proposals and found the right freelancer for the project, you can hire them by making an offer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Make an offer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Jobs tab. Locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Hire Freelancer button. And fill out the offer form.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The freelancer will receive a notification of your job offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>They could accept the offer and a contract will start. Or they could decline the offer and withdraw their proposal. Or they could message you to discuss alternative terms.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a contract has been started, you can find the active contract under Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Withdraw an offer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you changed your mind after making an offer, you can withdraw your offer so long as the freelancer hasn&rsquo;t already accepted it. If the freelancer has already accepted your offer, you&rsquo;ll need to end the contract under the Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw a pending offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want in your Pending Offers and click Withdraw Offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>After you&rsquo;ve reviewed proposals and found the right freelancer for the project, you can hire them by making an offer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Make an offer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Jobs tab. Locate the job you want in your Open Jobs and click View Applicants in the Actions menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Hire Freelancer button. And fill out the offer form.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The freelancer will receive a notification of your job offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>They could accept the offer and a contract will start. Or they could decline the offer and withdraw their proposal. Or they could message you to discuss alternative terms.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a contract has been started, you can find the active contract under Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Withdraw an offer<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you changed your mind after making an offer, you can withdraw your offer so long as the freelancer hasn&rsquo;t already accepted it. If the freelancer has already accepted your offer, you&rsquo;ll need to end the contract under the Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw a pending offer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the job you want in your Pending Offers and click Withdraw Offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 7, 0, 5, NULL, 'make-an-offer-to-hire-a-freelancer', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:43:48', '2018-06-07 15:43:48', NULL),
	(51, '{"en":"Rehire a Former Freelancer","ch":"Rehire a Former Freelancer"}', '{"en":"<p>You can easily rehire a former freelancer by making an offer. Once the freelancer receives and accepts your rehire offer, the contract begins.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Post a job and go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Freelancers<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the freelancer you want to rehire in Hired Freelancers or Saved Freelancers tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Hire button to make an offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make an offer, the freelancer can accept or decline your offer. If the freelancer declines, you may make a new offer. You can confirm that your new contract is active by going to Workroom &gt; My Contracts and check the list of Contracts.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can easily rehire a former freelancer by making an offer. Once the freelancer receives and accepts your rehire offer, the contract begins.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Post a job and go to Hire Freelancers &gt; My Freelancers<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the freelancer you want to rehire in Hired Freelancers or Saved Freelancers tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Hire button to make an offer.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make an offer, the freelancer can accept or decline your offer. If the freelancer declines, you may make a new offer. You can confirm that your new contract is active by going to Workroom &gt; My Contracts and check the list of Contracts.<\\/p>"}', 7, 0, 6, NULL, 'rehire-a-former-freelancer', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:44:20', '2018-06-07 15:44:20', NULL),
	(52, '{"en":"Workroom","ch":"Workroom"}', '{"en":"<p>In the workroom, you can collaborate on contracts with your freelancers. You can access through Workroom &gt; My Contracts pages by clicking the name of a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In workroom you can:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Pause \\/ Start that contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Make payments and review your billing history for that contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Send messages and files<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Access the original job post and proposals you received<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Review, and create new milestones for a fixed-price contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Check your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary for hourly contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Raise hourly rates, adjust weekly limits and allow\\/disallow manual time for hourly contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>End contract and leave feedback<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>In the workroom, you can collaborate on contracts with your freelancers. You can access through Workroom &gt; My Contracts pages by clicking the name of a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In workroom you can:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Pause \\/ Start that contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Make payments and review your billing history for that contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Send messages and files<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Access the original job post and proposals you received<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Review, and create new milestones for a fixed-price contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Check your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary for hourly contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Raise hourly rates, adjust weekly limits and allow\\/disallow manual time for hourly contracts<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>End contract and leave feedback<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 0, NULL, 'workroom', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:45:18', '2018-06-07 15:45:18', NULL),
	(53, '{"en":"Manual Time Logging for an Hourly Contract","ch":"Manual Time Logging for an Hourly Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>Freelancers often use the manual time to account for hours on offline tasks such as sketching or making phone calls, for example, or anything that can&rsquo;t be accurately represented on their Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers can decide whether or not their freelancers can bill manual time. They can then allow or disallow it on their contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you hire a freelancer, the &ldquo;Allow freelancer to log time manually if needed&rdquo; checkbox is selected by default. You have to deselect it to disable manual time for your freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can change it in Workroom of an hourly contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In overview tab, you can find Change link in Manual Time.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Change link to allow\\/disallow manual time.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Freelancers often use the manual time to account for hours on offline tasks such as sketching or making phone calls, for example, or anything that can&rsquo;t be accurately represented on their Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers can decide whether or not their freelancers can bill manual time. They can then allow or disallow it on their contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you hire a freelancer, the &ldquo;Allow freelancer to log time manually if needed&rdquo; checkbox is selected by default. You have to deselect it to disable manual time for your freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can change it in Workroom of an hourly contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In overview tab, you can find Change link in Manual Time.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Change link to allow\\/disallow manual time.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 1, NULL, 'manual-time-logging-for-an-hourly-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:45:57', '2018-06-07 15:45:57', NULL),
	(54, '{"en":"Set a Weekly Limit for an Hourly Contract","ch":"Set a Weekly Limit for an Hourly Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>You can easily manage your budget by setting up a weekly limit on the number of hours a freelancer can bill. When you increase a freelancer&rsquo;s weekly limit, the new limit takes effect immediately and hours already in your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary will count against that limit for the current week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you decrease a weekly limit, it won&rsquo;t take effect until the next work week (Monday at 00:00 UTC).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hours in excess of the limit will not be billed. In case you approve the work beyond the weekly limit, you can make a bonus payment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change a freelancer&rsquo;s weekly limit:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In overview tab, you can find Change link in Weekly Limit.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Change link and change the weekly limit.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can easily manage your budget by setting up a weekly limit on the number of hours a freelancer can bill. When you increase a freelancer&rsquo;s weekly limit, the new limit takes effect immediately and hours already in your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary will count against that limit for the current week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you decrease a weekly limit, it won&rsquo;t take effect until the next work week (Monday at 00:00 UTC).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hours in excess of the limit will not be billed. In case you approve the work beyond the weekly limit, you can make a bonus payment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change a freelancer&rsquo;s weekly limit:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In overview tab, you can find Change link in Weekly Limit.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Change link and change the weekly limit.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 2, NULL, 'set-a-weekly-limit-for-an-hourly-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:46:33', '2018-06-07 15:46:33', NULL),
	(55, '{"en":"Check your Freelancer\'s Work Diary","ch":"Check your Freelancer\'s Work Diary"}', '{"en":"<p>Every hourly contract has its own Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Work Diary is used to literally see what a freelancer is working on during the week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It shows a grid of work-in-progress snapshots in hourly rows, each representing a 10-minute billing segment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your freelancer&rsquo;s work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click Work Diary link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select the date you want to view in the center of the navigation bar.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hover your mouse over the screenshot thumbnail image for a larger preview or click it to view the full-size image.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can&rsquo;t add, delete, or edit time in your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries. Only freelancers can change their Work Diaries. When a freelancer makes manual changes to the Work Diary, including adding or removing time and editing memos, the changes update in your reports. The only time within the weekly limit on an hourly contract will be billed and included in reports.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The previous week&rsquo;s Work Diaries are locked, and therefore no longer editable. You have to check your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary regularly and communicate with your freelancer if something goes wrong.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The work diary is only a tool to see your freelancer&rsquo;s work. So you have to communicate expectations clearly and manage your project directly.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to read your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your freelancers will use the iJobDesk Desktop App to track their work for hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a freelancer tracks time using the iJobDesk Desktop App, a screenshot and activity summary captured by the App will be uploaded every 10 minutes. You can also agree to let your freelancers add manual time to represent work activity not captured by the iJobDesk Desktop App.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The memo bars in the Work Diary are color-coded to indicate the status:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Green - Auto-tracked time by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Yellow - Manual time not captured by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The meter records the total number of mouse clicks, scroll actions, and keystrokes per 10 minutes. It doesn&rsquo;t record what a freelancer clicked or typed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Activity levels will fluctuate depending on the task. Some tasks, such as reading, and thinking will show low activity.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Every hourly contract has its own Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Work Diary is used to literally see what a freelancer is working on during the week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It shows a grid of work-in-progress snapshots in hourly rows, each representing a 10-minute billing segment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your freelancer&rsquo;s work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click Work Diary link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select the date you want to view in the center of the navigation bar.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hover your mouse over the screenshot thumbnail image for a larger preview or click it to view the full-size image.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can&rsquo;t add, delete, or edit time in your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries. Only freelancers can change their Work Diaries. When a freelancer makes manual changes to the Work Diary, including adding or removing time and editing memos, the changes update in your reports. The only time within the weekly limit on an hourly contract will be billed and included in reports.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The previous week&rsquo;s Work Diaries are locked, and therefore no longer editable. You have to check your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary regularly and communicate with your freelancer if something goes wrong.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The work diary is only a tool to see your freelancer&rsquo;s work. So you have to communicate expectations clearly and manage your project directly.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to read your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your freelancers will use the iJobDesk Desktop App to track their work for hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a freelancer tracks time using the iJobDesk Desktop App, a screenshot and activity summary captured by the App will be uploaded every 10 minutes. You can also agree to let your freelancers add manual time to represent work activity not captured by the iJobDesk Desktop App.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The memo bars in the Work Diary are color-coded to indicate the status:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Green - Auto-tracked time by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Yellow - Manual time not captured by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The meter records the total number of mouse clicks, scroll actions, and keystrokes per 10 minutes. It doesn&rsquo;t record what a freelancer clicked or typed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Activity levels will fluctuate depending on the task. Some tasks, such as reading, and thinking will show low activity.<\\/p>"}', 8, 0, 3, NULL, 'check-your-freelancers-work-diary', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:47:01', '2018-06-07 15:47:01', NULL),
	(56, '{"en":"Pause a Contract","ch":"Pause a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>You can temporarily pause a contract to stop a freelancer from logging more hours or wait until you are ready for the next part of your project. You can immediately restart your contract too.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To pause a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Pause Contract button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To restart the contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Start Again button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can temporarily pause a contract to stop a freelancer from logging more hours or wait until you are ready for the next part of your project. You can immediately restart your contract too.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To pause a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Pause Contract button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To restart the contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Start Again button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 4, NULL, 'pause-a-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:47:31', '2018-06-07 15:47:31', NULL),
	(57, '{"en":"Weekly Billing Summary","ch":"Weekly Billing Summary"}', '{"en":"<p>Your weekly billing summary includes all your charges from the past week. It has 3 sections: Timesheets for hourly contracts, Milestone Payments for fixed-price contracts, and all Other Payments (like bonuses).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Timesheets for hourly contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Timesheets for hourly contracts are billed automatically each Monday at 00:00 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This means your account will be charged each Monday for the previous week&rsquo;s work. Automatic billing includes the hours in your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you have a problem with this Timesheet or Work Diary, you may file a dispute on the contract detail page from the time you are billed on Monday until Friday at 23:59 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Milestone Payments for fixed-price contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>You can break a fixed-price contract into smaller milestones for easier billing and management.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You&rsquo;ll describe each of these milestones so that it is clear what the freelancer must deliver to earn payment for that milestone. And you fund the current milestone into iJobDesk Escrow so that the freelancer knows their payment is secure and ready to be released when the work is completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may create as many milestones as you need. You can check the milestone deliverables and release funds when you are 100% satisfied with the deliverables.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Other Payments<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make payments to your freelancers such as bonuses or manual payments, it will appear in this section.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Your weekly billing summary includes all your charges from the past week. It has 3 sections: Timesheets for hourly contracts, Milestone Payments for fixed-price contracts, and all Other Payments (like bonuses).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Timesheets for hourly contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Timesheets for hourly contracts are billed automatically each Monday at 00:00 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This means your account will be charged each Monday for the previous week&rsquo;s work. Automatic billing includes the hours in your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you have a problem with this Timesheet or Work Diary, you may file a dispute on the contract detail page from the time you are billed on Monday until Friday at 23:59 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Milestone Payments for fixed-price contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>You can break a fixed-price contract into smaller milestones for easier billing and management.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You&rsquo;ll describe each of these milestones so that it is clear what the freelancer must deliver to earn payment for that milestone. And you fund the current milestone into iJobDesk Escrow so that the freelancer knows their payment is secure and ready to be released when the work is completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may create as many milestones as you need. You can check the milestone deliverables and release funds when you are 100% satisfied with the deliverables.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Other Payments<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make payments to your freelancers such as bonuses or manual payments, it will appear in this section.<\\/p>"}', 8, 0, 5, NULL, 'weekly-billing-summary', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:47:57', '2018-06-07 15:47:57', NULL),
	(58, '{"en":"Reports","ch":"Reports"}', '{"en":"<p>Reports help you see what your freelancers are working on currently and support simple ways to track how many hours your freelancers log and payments you have made.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Work Diary - To see what a freelancer is working on during the week<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Weekly Summary - A billing summary that includes payments for hourly and fixed-price contracts, and other payments<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timesheet - Hours and cost totaled in days, weeks, or months<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Transactions - A detailed record of your payments<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Reports help you see what your freelancers are working on currently and support simple ways to track how many hours your freelancers log and payments you have made.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Work Diary - To see what a freelancer is working on during the week<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Weekly Summary - A billing summary that includes payments for hourly and fixed-price contracts, and other payments<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timesheet - Hours and cost totaled in days, weeks, or months<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Transactions - A detailed record of your payments<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 6, NULL, 'reports', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:48:29', '2018-06-07 15:48:29', NULL),
	(59, '{"en":"End a Contract","ch":"End a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>All users have the freedom to end a contract at any time. But it is always best to talk to your freelancers first to let them know what&rsquo;s going on.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to consider the following before you end a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The system locks your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary immediately. So your freelancer cannot edit their Work Diary.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You will be billed for your freelancer&rsquo;s hours tracked. But you may dispute them according to the usual weekly billing cycle.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Both of you and your freelancer can leave feedback. Your freelancer can&rsquo;t see the feedback you left them until after they have left feedback for you.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To end a contract:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Cancel Contract if you don&rsquo;t make any payment.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End Contract if you paid.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For an hourly contract, you may give your freelancer the opportunity to check the current week&rsquo;s Work Diary and make adjustments, if necessary. This can help you both avoid a dispute later.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For a fixed-price contract, you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to make a payment after you end the contract.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>All users have the freedom to end a contract at any time. But it is always best to talk to your freelancers first to let them know what&rsquo;s going on.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to consider the following before you end a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The system locks your freelancer&rsquo;s Work Diary immediately. So your freelancer cannot edit their Work Diary.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You will be billed for your freelancer&rsquo;s hours tracked. But you may dispute them according to the usual weekly billing cycle.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Both of you and your freelancer can leave feedback. Your freelancer can&rsquo;t see the feedback you left them until after they have left feedback for you.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>To end a contract:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Cancel Contract if you don&rsquo;t make any payment.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End Contract if you paid.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For an hourly contract, you may give your freelancer the opportunity to check the current week&rsquo;s Work Diary and make adjustments, if necessary. This can help you both avoid a dispute later.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For a fixed-price contract, you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to make a payment after you end the contract.<\\/p>"}', 8, 0, 7, NULL, 'end-a-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:48:54', '2018-06-07 15:48:54', NULL),
	(60, '{"en":"Feedback","ch":"Feedback"}', '{"en":"<h4>Give feedback to Freelancers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you end a contract, you can leave feedback in the End Contract form. If the freelancer ended the contract, you&rsquo;ll have 14 days to leave feedback. Both parties can leave feedback for a contract that the payments have been made through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The feedback period is 14 days from the end of a contract. The feedback system is double-blind, which means that feedback won&rsquo;t be visible until both parties provide it for each other. In case only one party leaves feedback, it will be posted after the 14-day period has expired.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To give feedback to your freelancer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Contract Detail Page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End Contract button and give feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Read feedback from Freelancers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your feedback that you received from freelancers show on every project you post to help freelancers evaluate you.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your feedback received:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Contract Detail Page<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click feedback tab to see the feedback<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<h4>Give feedback to Freelancers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you end a contract, you can leave feedback in the End Contract form. If the freelancer ended the contract, you&rsquo;ll have 14 days to leave feedback. Both parties can leave feedback for a contract that the payments have been made through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The feedback period is 14 days from the end of a contract. The feedback system is double-blind, which means that feedback won&rsquo;t be visible until both parties provide it for each other. In case only one party leaves feedback, it will be posted after the 14-day period has expired.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To give feedback to your freelancer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Contract Detail Page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End Contract button and give feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Read feedback from Freelancers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your feedback that you received from freelancers show on every project you post to help freelancers evaluate you.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your feedback received:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Contract Detail Page<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click feedback tab to see the feedback<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 8, 0, 8, NULL, 'feedback', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:49:22', '2018-06-07 15:49:22', NULL),
	(61, '{"en":"File a dispute for a Contract","ch":"File a dispute for a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>Majority of work done on iJobDesk goes smoothly for both parties, but it&rsquo;s inevitable that an occasional dispute arise. We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you file a dispute, please consider the following:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The contract will be suspended automatically.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You should only file a dispute when working the matter out with your freelancer has failed.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please contact the freelancer to ask them to delete the improperly-logged time from the Work Diary. If it is too late for the freelancer to edit the Work Diary, ask for a refund.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>For a fixed-price contract, you should release funds in Escrow when you are 100% satisfied with the milestone deliverables. If you have a problem after funds are released, you can talk to your freelancer about a refund before you file a dispute.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If a contract has been ended, you have 14 days from the end of a contract to file a dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To file a dispute for a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In Overview tab, you can find File a Dispute link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the link, fill out the form and submit it<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>iJobDesk sends your freelancer a notification of the dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves. If it is solved smoothly themselves, iJobDesk takes no action and the contract will be restarted.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the freelancer rejects the dispute, it enters arbitration. In case the freelancer doesn&rsquo;t respond within seven days, an iJobDesk Dispute Specialist refunds all disputed amount and end the dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Both parties are required to add detailed information about the dispute, which the iJobDesk Dispute Specialist reviews and evaluates them. iJobDesk will carefully consider any information presented.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your freelancer won&rsquo;t have access to the funds until an iJobDesk Dispute Manager makes a decision on the case.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a dispute is awarded in your favor, we credit the refund to your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Majority of work done on iJobDesk goes smoothly for both parties, but it&rsquo;s inevitable that an occasional dispute arise. We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before you file a dispute, please consider the following:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The contract will be suspended automatically.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You should only file a dispute when working the matter out with your freelancer has failed.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please contact the freelancer to ask them to delete the improperly-logged time from the Work Diary. If it is too late for the freelancer to edit the Work Diary, ask for a refund.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>For a fixed-price contract, you should release funds in Escrow when you are 100% satisfied with the milestone deliverables. If you have a problem after funds are released, you can talk to your freelancer about a refund before you file a dispute.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If a contract has been ended, you have 14 days from the end of a contract to file a dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To file a dispute for a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts, locate the contract and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In Overview tab, you can find File a Dispute link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the link, fill out the form and submit it<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>iJobDesk sends your freelancer a notification of the dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves. If it is solved smoothly themselves, iJobDesk takes no action and the contract will be restarted.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the freelancer rejects the dispute, it enters arbitration. In case the freelancer doesn&rsquo;t respond within seven days, an iJobDesk Dispute Specialist refunds all disputed amount and end the dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Both parties are required to add detailed information about the dispute, which the iJobDesk Dispute Specialist reviews and evaluates them. iJobDesk will carefully consider any information presented.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your freelancer won&rsquo;t have access to the funds until an iJobDesk Dispute Manager makes a decision on the case.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a dispute is awarded in your favor, we credit the refund to your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>"}', 9, 0, 0, NULL, 'file-a-dispute-for-a-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:49:58', '2018-06-07 15:49:58', NULL),
	(62, '{"en":"iJobDesk Payment Protection","ch":"iJobDesk Payment Protection"}', '{"en":"<p>iJobDesk Payment Protection helps give security and peace of mind to buyers and freelancers working together on projects.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For fixed-price contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a buyer pays a freelancer for deliverables rather than by the hour, iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection helps ensure that buyers get the work they&rsquo;ve asked for and freelancers get paid for work they completed. Buyers will deposit a milestone payment into iJobDesk Escrow before work begins.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Upon receiving and approving the work, the funds in escrow will be released to the freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For hourly contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a buyer pays a freelancer by the hour, iJobDesk doesn&rsquo;t support Payment Protection at the moment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers should have funds enough in their iJobDesk Accounts to let your freelancers work on hourly contracts. In case the buyer has insufficient funds in their accounts, the freelancer will be notified every time the iJobDesk Desktop Application captures their activities.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>iJobDesk Payment Protection helps give security and peace of mind to buyers and freelancers working together on projects.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For fixed-price contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a buyer pays a freelancer for deliverables rather than by the hour, iJobDesk Fixed-Price Protection helps ensure that buyers get the work they&rsquo;ve asked for and freelancers get paid for work they completed. Buyers will deposit a milestone payment into iJobDesk Escrow before work begins.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Upon receiving and approving the work, the funds in escrow will be released to the freelancer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>For hourly contracts<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a buyer pays a freelancer by the hour, iJobDesk doesn&rsquo;t support Payment Protection at the moment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers should have funds enough in their iJobDesk Accounts to let your freelancers work on hourly contracts. In case the buyer has insufficient funds in their accounts, the freelancer will be notified every time the iJobDesk Desktop Application captures their activities.<\\/p>"}', 10, 20, 0, 0, 'ijobdesk-payment-protection', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:50:45', '2018-06-08 02:14:57', NULL),
	(63, '{"en":"Deposit Funds to Your iJobDesk.com Account","ch":"Deposit Funds to Your iJobDesk.com Account"}', '{"en":"<p>In order to pay freelancers and upgrade jobs, buyers need to have funds available in their accounts. The buyers can make a deposit. It means putting funds on your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To deposit funds:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Deposit Funds.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Deposit Now button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you don&rsquo;t have valid payment method added, you have to add a payment method before depositing.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/payment-methods\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to add a payment method.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>In order to pay freelancers and upgrade jobs, buyers need to have funds available in their accounts. The buyers can make a deposit. It means putting funds on your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To deposit funds:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and click Deposit Funds.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Deposit Now button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you don&rsquo;t have valid payment method added, you have to add a payment method before depositing.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/account\\/payment-methods\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to add a payment method.<\\/p>"}', 10, 0, 1, NULL, 'deposit-funds-to-your-ijobdeskcom-account', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:51:23', '2018-06-12 13:44:56', NULL),
	(64, '{"en":"Pay for Fixed-Price Contracts","ch":"Pay for Fixed-Price Contracts"}', '{"en":"<p>When you work with a freelancer on a fixed-price contract you need to make escrow deposits as the contract proceeds so that payments can be released to your freelancer when you accept and approve the deliverables.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Escrow deposits<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make escrow deposits, the freelancer knows their payment is secure and ready to be released when the work is completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can make escrow deposits when:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hiring freelancer - When you submit an offer to a freelancer and create your first milestone.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Working - After you create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Release Funds<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please ensure you are 100% satisfied with work submitted for a milestone before releasing the payment to your freelancer. When funds are released to the freelancer, the system moves funds from Escrow to the freelancer account. If you are not satisfied with the work your freelancer submitted, please request changes by describing the changes needed in the Message Room.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Create another milestone (Optional)<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you have more work for your freelancer, you can keep the contract open and create another milestone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can make escrow deposits for the milestone immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Give a bonus<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can give a bonus to your freelancer on the contract detail page.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>When you work with a freelancer on a fixed-price contract you need to make escrow deposits as the contract proceeds so that payments can be released to your freelancer when you accept and approve the deliverables.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Escrow deposits<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you make escrow deposits, the freelancer knows their payment is secure and ready to be released when the work is completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can make escrow deposits when:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hiring freelancer - When you submit an offer to a freelancer and create your first milestone.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Working - After you create milestones.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Release Funds<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please ensure you are 100% satisfied with work submitted for a milestone before releasing the payment to your freelancer. When funds are released to the freelancer, the system moves funds from Escrow to the freelancer account. If you are not satisfied with the work your freelancer submitted, please request changes by describing the changes needed in the Message Room.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Create another milestone (Optional)<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you have more work for your freelancer, you can keep the contract open and create another milestone.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can make escrow deposits for the milestone immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Give a bonus<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can give a bonus to your freelancer on the contract detail page.<\\/p>"}', 10, 0, 2, NULL, 'pay-for-fixed-price-contracts', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:52:41', '2018-06-07 15:52:41', NULL),
	(65, '{"en":"Pay for Hourly Contracts","ch":"Pay for Hourly Contracts"}', '{"en":"<p>Every Monday your account will be charged automatically for the previous week&rsquo;s hours based on your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries. If there&rsquo;s an issue, you have until Friday to file a dispute. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Give a bonus<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can give a bonus to your freelancer on the contract detail page<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Every Monday your account will be charged automatically for the previous week&rsquo;s hours based on your freelancers&rsquo; Work Diaries. If there&rsquo;s an issue, you have until Friday to file a dispute. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Give a bonus<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can give a bonus to your freelancer on the contract detail page<\\/p>"}', 10, 0, 3, NULL, 'pay-for-hourly-contracts', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:53:19', '2018-06-07 15:53:19', NULL),
	(66, '{"en":"Get a Refund on a Contract","ch":"Get a Refund on a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>You have to contact your freelancer to request a refund. Freelancers can choose to give a refund for any contract for payments made.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the refund causes the contract to generate less than $1.00 in total earnings, the contract won&rsquo;t show on your work history (or on your freelancer&rsquo;s) and any feedback will be removed. It can take up to 24 hours for both histories to reflect changes due to refunds.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Freelancers may only refund an amount that is less than or equal to what they earned on the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To check any refunds that you have received, go to Reports &gt; Transactions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If your freelancer refused your refund request or did not respond, please file a dispute. If we determine that your freelancer&rsquo;s hours don&rsquo;t qualify for the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Payment Protection<\\/a>, the dispute will be resolved in your favor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/file-a-dispute-for-a-contract\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to see how to file a dispute.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You have to contact your freelancer to request a refund. Freelancers can choose to give a refund for any contract for payments made.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the refund causes the contract to generate less than $1.00 in total earnings, the contract won&rsquo;t show on your work history (or on your freelancer&rsquo;s) and any feedback will be removed. It can take up to 24 hours for both histories to reflect changes due to refunds.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Freelancers may only refund an amount that is less than or equal to what they earned on the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To check any refunds that you have received, go to Reports &gt; Transactions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If your freelancer refused your refund request or did not respond, please file a dispute. If we determine that your freelancer&rsquo;s hours don&rsquo;t qualify for the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Payment Protection<\\/a>, the dispute will be resolved in your favor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Click <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/file-a-dispute-for-a-contract\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here<\\/a> to see how to file a dispute.<\\/p>"}', 10, 0, 4, NULL, 'get-a-refund-on-a-contract', 2, 1, '2018-06-07 15:53:53', '2018-06-07 15:53:53', NULL),
	(67, '{"en":"Payment Methods","ch":"Payment Methods"}', '{"en":"<p>You can add payment methods as many as you like.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a payment method:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Add a Payment Method button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It supports the following payment methods:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Paypal<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Credit Card<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Wechat<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Bank<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Skrill<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can delete payment methods anytime. If you add multiple payment methods, you can set primary payment method that you can use when you make deposits.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For security reasons, your new payment method will become active in three days.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can add payment methods as many as you like.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a payment method:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Add a Payment Method button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It supports the following payment methods:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Paypal<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Credit Card<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Wechat<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Bank<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Skrill<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can delete payment methods anytime. If you add multiple payment methods, you can set primary payment method that you can use when you make deposits.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For security reasons, your new payment method will become active in three days.<\\/p>"}', 11, 22, 0, 0, 'payment-methods', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:56:06', '2018-06-08 02:24:59', NULL),
	(68, '{"en":"Add a PayPal Account","ch":"Add a PayPal Account"}', '{"en":"<p>To add a PayPal Account:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Add a Payment Method button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose PayPal and enter PayPal Account information.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For security reasons, your new PayPal account will become active on the iJobDesk marketplace in three days.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal is a third-party payment vendor. PayPal&rsquo;s features and fees vary depending on your location.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>To add a PayPal Account:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Add a Payment Method button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose PayPal and enter PayPal Account information.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For security reasons, your new PayPal account will become active on the iJobDesk marketplace in three days.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal is a third-party payment vendor. PayPal&rsquo;s features and fees vary depending on your location.<\\/p>"}', 11, 22, 1, 1, 'add-a-paypal-account', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:56:58', '2018-06-08 02:26:13', NULL),
	(69, '{"en":"Edit or Remove Payment Methods","ch":"Edit or Remove Payment Methods"}', '{"en":"<p>You can edit your payment methods any time you wish.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To edit your payment methods:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here, you can remove, edit, change your payment method.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may edit your credit card details, but you cannot edit the credit card number. If your credit card number has changed, please remove the invalid credit card and add your credit card as a new payment method.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your PayPal accounts. You have to remove the old PayPal payment method and add a new PayPal account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your Skrill accounts. You have to remove the old Skrill payment method and add a new Skrill account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your Wechat accounts. You have to remove the old Wechat payment method and add a new Wechat account.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can edit your payment methods any time you wish.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To edit your payment methods:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here, you can remove, edit, change your payment method.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may edit your credit card details, but you cannot edit the credit card number. If your credit card number has changed, please remove the invalid credit card and add your credit card as a new payment method.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your PayPal accounts. You have to remove the old PayPal payment method and add a new PayPal account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your Skrill accounts. You have to remove the old Skrill payment method and add a new Skrill account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot edit your Wechat accounts. You have to remove the old Wechat payment method and add a new Wechat account.<\\/p>"}', 11, 22, 2, 2, 'edit-or-remove-payment-methods', 0, 1, '2018-06-07 15:57:48', '2018-06-08 02:25:55', NULL),
	(70, '{"en":"Getting Started as a Freelancer","ch":"Getting Started as a Freelancer"}', '{"en":"<p>Getting started as a freelancer on iJobDesk is simple.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/signup\\/freelancer\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Sign up<\\/a> link on iJobDesk.com home page. On the signup page, provide your name, email address, username and password. Read our <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/privacy-policy\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Privacy Policy<\\/a>. Create an account by submitting and then confirm your email address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Complete your freelancer profile (including skills, portfolio, etc.), which serves as your iJobDesk resume and is your most powerful tool for getting hired.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/search\\/jobs\\" target=\\"_blank\\">find jobs<\\/a> you are interested and submit proposals to the jobs.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You should check the status of proposals, and Messages tab and Notifications tab often.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You are now ready to be a Freelancer at iJobDesk.com!<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Getting started as a freelancer on iJobDesk is simple.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/signup\\/freelancer\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Sign up<\\/a> link on iJobDesk.com home page. On the signup page, provide your name, email address, username and password. Read our <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/terms\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Terms and Conditions<\\/a> and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/privacy-policy\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Privacy Policy<\\/a>. Create an account by submitting and then confirm your email address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Complete your freelancer profile (including skills, portfolio, etc.), which serves as your iJobDesk resume and is your most powerful tool for getting hired.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/search\\/jobs\\" target=\\"_blank\\">find jobs<\\/a> you are interested and submit proposals to the jobs.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You should check the status of proposals, and Messages tab and Notifications tab often.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You are now ready to be a Freelancer at iJobDesk.com!<\\/p>"}', 1, 0, 1, NULL, 'getting-started-as-a-freelancer', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:29:49', '2018-06-08 03:20:35', NULL),
	(71, '{"en":"Create a Freelancer Profile","ch":"Create a Freelancer Profile"}', '{"en":"<p>You need to create a 100% complete freelancer profile to start working on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To create a profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n    <li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to complete the following parts:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n    <li>About Me<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Portfolio<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Certifications<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Employment History<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Educations<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Other Experiences<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please provide accurate information about you and build your reputation on iJobDesk Marketplace.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You need to create a 100% complete freelancer profile to start working on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To create a profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n    <li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have to complete the following parts:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n    <li>About Me<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Portfolio<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Certifications<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Employment History<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Educations<\\/li>\\r\\n    <li>Other Experiences<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please provide accurate information about you and build your reputation on iJobDesk Marketplace.<\\/p>"}', 12, 0, 0, NULL, 'create-a-freelancer-profile', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:31:44', '2018-06-08 01:31:44', NULL),
	(72, '{"en":"Create a Profile Title","ch":"Create a Profile Title"}', '{"en":"<p>The title of your profile is your first impression to potential buyers and it allows you to share your top skills and area of expertise. So you have to make it descriptive about your skills and highlight your primary talents (do not include every skill you have).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update a title:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Edit button (pencil icon) next to your Title.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>The title of your profile is your first impression to potential buyers and it allows you to share your top skills and area of expertise. So you have to make it descriptive about your skills and highlight your primary talents (do not include every skill you have).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update a title:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Edit button (pencil icon) next to your Title.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 1, NULL, 'create-a-profile-title', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:32:22', '2018-06-08 01:32:22', NULL),
	(73, '{"en":"Add Portrait","ch":"Add Portrait"}', '{"en":"<p>You can add your portrait to your freelancer profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You profile portrait must be a clear, headshot-style photo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a portrait to your profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can add your portrait to your freelancer profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You profile portrait must be a clear, headshot-style photo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a portrait to your profile:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 2, NULL, 'add-portrait', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:32:54', '2018-06-08 04:28:53', NULL),
	(74, '{"en":"Set Hourly Rate","ch":"Set Hourly Rate"}', '{"en":"<p>It is an important part of your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers will filter freelancers by hourly rate when they search for freelancers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your hourly rate gives buyers an idea of how much you generally charge.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can change it as often as you like. It won&rsquo;t affect your current contracts or submitted proposals.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may negotiate new hourly rate when the buyer interviews you for a job.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To set your hourly rate:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter your rate (what the buyer sees and pays). The form will subtract the iJobDesk Service Fee to estimate your net earnings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Save.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>It is an important part of your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers will filter freelancers by hourly rate when they search for freelancers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your hourly rate gives buyers an idea of how much you generally charge.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can change it as often as you like. It won&rsquo;t affect your current contracts or submitted proposals.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may negotiate new hourly rate when the buyer interviews you for a job.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To set your hourly rate:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter your rate (what the buyer sees and pays). The form will subtract the iJobDesk Service Fee to estimate your net earnings.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Save.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 3, NULL, 'set-hourly-rate', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:33:26', '2018-06-08 01:33:26', NULL),
	(75, '{"en":"Set Availability","ch":"Set Availability"}', '{"en":"<p>You can avoid the frustration of dealing with invitations when you are not looking for more work on iJobDesk. To avoid such situation, you update your availability when you accept new work, a contract ends, or your life gets too busy.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Keeping your availability updated can help you to access the most relevant jobs.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update your availability:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can update your availability anytime.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can avoid the frustration of dealing with invitations when you are not looking for more work on iJobDesk. To avoid such situation, you update your availability when you accept new work, a contract ends, or your life gets too busy.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Keeping your availability updated can help you to access the most relevant jobs.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update your availability:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can update your availability anytime.<\\/p>"}', 12, 0, 4, NULL, 'set-availability', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:34:01', '2018-06-08 01:34:01', NULL),
	(76, '{"en":"Set Visibility","ch":"Set Visibility"}', '{"en":"<p>Your profile visibility settings allow you to decide where and when buyers can see your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you change your visibility settings, it can take up to one day for the change to be viewable on the iJobDesk website and several days for the change to take effect with search engines.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you wish to avoid receiving invitations or offers, you can <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/set-availability\\" target=\\"_blank\\">change your availability<\\/a> as Not Available.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change your profile visibility:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here come details of potential visibility options:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Public - Your profile will be visible to the public including buyers, freelancers, and visitors.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Only iJobDesk Users - Only logged-in iJobDesk users can find your profile and it&rsquo;s hidden from search engines.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Private - Your profile will be hidden from the iJobDesk marketplace and search engines. Your profile will be accessible only through your proposals or contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Your profile visibility settings allow you to decide where and when buyers can see your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you change your visibility settings, it can take up to one day for the change to be viewable on the iJobDesk website and several days for the change to take effect with search engines.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you wish to avoid receiving invitations or offers, you can <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/set-availability\\" target=\\"_blank\\">change your availability<\\/a> as Not Available.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To change your profile visibility:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here come details of potential visibility options:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Public - Your profile will be visible to the public including buyers, freelancers, and visitors.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Only iJobDesk Users - Only logged-in iJobDesk users can find your profile and it&rsquo;s hidden from search engines.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Private - Your profile will be hidden from the iJobDesk marketplace and search engines. Your profile will be accessible only through your proposals or contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 5, NULL, 'set-visibility', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:51:35', '2018-06-08 01:51:35', NULL),
	(77, '{"en":"Add Profile Overview","ch":"Add Profile Overview"}', '{"en":"<p>Keep it brief, and never include your contact information in your overview.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your overview sets the tone for your profile by showing off your personality.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add an overview:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Overview section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type or paste in the message what you want buyers to see about you first and click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Keep it brief, and never include your contact information in your overview.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your overview sets the tone for your profile by showing off your personality.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add an overview:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Overview section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type or paste in the message what you want buyers to see about you first and click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 6, NULL, 'add-profile-overview', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:52:06', '2018-06-08 01:52:06', NULL),
	(78, '{"en":"Add Skills","ch":"Add Skills"}', '{"en":"<p>Please add your skills to let your buyers learn if you are the right person for potential projects.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a skill:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Skills section<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Start typing the name of a skill, then select the best match from the list provided. If you want to enter more skills, repeat this step for each.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You can rank or order your skills. This order is how they will appear in your profile.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Please add your skills to let your buyers learn if you are the right person for potential projects.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a skill:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Skills section<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Start typing the name of a skill, then select the best match from the list provided. If you want to enter more skills, repeat this step for each.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>You can rank or order your skills. This order is how they will appear in your profile.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 7, NULL, 'add-skills', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:53:03', '2018-06-08 01:53:03', NULL),
	(79, '{"en":"Add English Proficiency","ch":"Add English Proficiency"}', '{"en":"<p>English is most common language to communicate all around the world and iJobDesk is operated in English and Chinese. Setting a self-assessed English proficiency is required when you set up your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Setting appropriate English proficiency will make it easy to satisfy your buyers, and inappropriate expectations could adversely impact your reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update English Proficiency:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll to the English Level section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Specify your proficiency. And click the save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>English is most common language to communicate all around the world and iJobDesk is operated in English and Chinese. Setting a self-assessed English proficiency is required when you set up your profile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Setting appropriate English proficiency will make it easy to satisfy your buyers, and inappropriate expectations could adversely impact your reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update English Proficiency:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll to the English Level section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Specify your proficiency. And click the save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 8, NULL, 'add-english-proficiency', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:53:32', '2018-06-08 01:53:32', NULL),
	(80, '{"en":"Add Other Languages","ch":"Add Other Languages"}', '{"en":"<p>You can add other languages besides English. Some projects may require the ability to read and write certain languages. Please include all languages that you feel comfortable communicating to make your profile stand out to global buyers on iJobDesk Marketplace.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add other languages than English:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll to the Languages section and add languages.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can add other languages besides English. Some projects may require the ability to read and write certain languages. Please include all languages that you feel comfortable communicating to make your profile stand out to global buyers on iJobDesk Marketplace.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add other languages than English:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll to the Languages section and add languages.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 9, NULL, 'add-other-languages', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:54:02', '2018-06-08 01:54:02', NULL),
	(81, '{"en":"Add Portfolios","ch":"Add Portfolios"}', '{"en":"<p>You can add real-life examples of your skills and expertise to impress potential buyers. It should be projects related to any or all of your skills, so long as you personally have worked.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can add your best work rather than everything you have ever worked. And highlight skills and technologies for projects, and describe your role in the projects. Please keep your portfolio updated.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a project to your portfolio:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Portfolio section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fill the content and click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can add real-life examples of your skills and expertise to impress potential buyers. It should be projects related to any or all of your skills, so long as you personally have worked.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can add your best work rather than everything you have ever worked. And highlight skills and technologies for projects, and describe your role in the projects. Please keep your portfolio updated.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a project to your portfolio:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Portfolio section.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fill the content and click Save button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 10, NULL, 'add-portfolios', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:54:42', '2018-06-08 01:54:42', NULL),
	(82, '{"en":"Add Certifications","ch":"Add Certifications"}', '{"en":"<p>You may show off your skills, experience, and qualifications by adding certifications that you&rsquo;ve earned outside of iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a certification:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Certifications section and click the Add button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You may show off your skills, experience, and qualifications by adding certifications that you&rsquo;ve earned outside of iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add a certification:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Certifications section and click the Add button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 11, NULL, 'add-certifications', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:55:11', '2018-06-08 01:55:11', NULL),
	(83, '{"en":"Add Employment History","ch":"Add Employment History"}', '{"en":"<p>You can use your work history to build your portfolio to establish the credibility.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your iJobDesk contracts will appear in your work history automatically. So you need to add other work histories in this section. You may include student jobs, internships and other work histories outside of iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add employment history:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Employment History section and click the Add button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can use your work history to build your portfolio to establish the credibility.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your iJobDesk contracts will appear in your work history automatically. So you need to add other work histories in this section. You may include student jobs, internships and other work histories outside of iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add employment history:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Employment History section and click the Add button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 12, NULL, 'add-employment-history', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:57:00', '2018-06-08 01:57:00', NULL),
	(84, '{"en":"Add Other Experiences","ch":"Add Other Experiences"}', '{"en":"<p>You may add anything that doesn&rsquo;t fit into the other sections of your profile to this section. These may relevant to the types of jobs you are looking for on iJobDesk. You may include personal interests, informal education, or other background information that helps support your expertise and experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add other experiences:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Other Experiences section and click the Add button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You may add anything that doesn&rsquo;t fit into the other sections of your profile to this section. These may relevant to the types of jobs you are looking for on iJobDesk. You may include personal interests, informal education, or other background information that helps support your expertise and experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add other experiences:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu, and then click My Profile link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Scroll down to the Other Experiences section and click the Add button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 13, NULL, 'add-other-experiences', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:57:30', '2018-06-08 01:57:30', NULL),
	(85, '{"en":"Change My Name","ch":"Change My Name"}', '{"en":"<p>You must use your real, verifiable name according to iJobDesk&rsquo;s Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Note: You are not allowed to transfer accounts from one person to another on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To edit your name:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Click &quot;My Account&quot; to edit your name.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You must use your real, verifiable name according to iJobDesk&rsquo;s Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Note: You are not allowed to transfer accounts from one person to another on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To edit your name:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Click &quot;My Account&quot; to edit your name.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 14, NULL, 'change-my-name', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:57:57', '2018-06-08 01:57:57', NULL),
	(86, '{"en":"Edit My Account Information","ch":"Edit My Account Information"}', '{"en":"<p>To edit your account information:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Click &quot;My Account&quot;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You should provide accurate information about yourself.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please be careful when you update your account information:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Email address - Please be sure to use an address you check frequently.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>User ID - It cannot be edited. You&rsquo;ve set it up when you registered.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Name - You must use your real, verifiable name.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Address - You must use your real, permanent address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Country - You must be logged into iJobDesk from the country.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>To edit your account information:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Click &quot;My Account&quot;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You should provide accurate information about yourself.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please be careful when you update your account information:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Email address - Please be sure to use an address you check frequently.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>User ID - It cannot be edited. You&rsquo;ve set it up when you registered.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Name - You must use your real, verifiable name.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Address - You must use your real, permanent address.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Country - You must be logged into iJobDesk from the country.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 12, 0, 15, NULL, 'edit-my-account-information', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:58:26', '2018-06-08 01:58:26', NULL),
	(87, '{"en":"Search for Jobs","ch":"Search for Jobs"}', '{"en":"<p>You can easily search for the projects that match your skills in several different ways.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may try several search combinations and a variety of filters to find the jobs you are looking for.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To search for jobs:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Find Jobs &gt; Find Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type a basic keyword search in the box, or click the Advanced Search link for more options.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>On the Search Results page, use the filters on the left to further narrow your results.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can easily search for the projects that match your skills in several different ways.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may try several search combinations and a variety of filters to find the jobs you are looking for.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To search for jobs:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Find Jobs &gt; Find Jobs.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type a basic keyword search in the box, or click the Advanced Search link for more options.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>On the Search Results page, use the filters on the left to further narrow your results.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 0, NULL, 'search-for-jobs', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 01:59:44', '2018-06-08 02:06:23', NULL),
	(88, '{"en":"Submit a Proposal","ch":"Submit a Proposal"}', '{"en":"<p>After you find a project you like, you can submit a proposal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To submit a proposal:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Submit a Proposal button on the right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Set your terms including the budget for the fixed-price project or hourly rate for the hourly project.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Write a cover letter to the buyer. You can use this opportunity to tell the buyer why they should want to work with you on this project.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Answer any questions the buyer may ask.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Add attachment. You can add some work samples to your proposal when you submit.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Submit a Proposal button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>After you find a project you like, you can submit a proposal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To submit a proposal:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Submit a Proposal button on the right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Set your terms including the budget for the fixed-price project or hourly rate for the hourly project.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Write a cover letter to the buyer. You can use this opportunity to tell the buyer why they should want to work with you on this project.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Answer any questions the buyer may ask.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Add attachment. You can add some work samples to your proposal when you submit.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Submit a Proposal button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 1, NULL, 'submit-a-proposal', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:00:14', '2018-06-08 02:06:32', NULL),
	(89, '{"en":"Featured Proposal","ch":"Featured Proposal"}', '{"en":"<p>The Featured Proposal is designed to help freelancers get noticed by buyers. It will put your proposal on top of the proposals when the buyer reviews the proposals from freelancers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Proposals are ranked in a job&rsquo;s proposal list based on their submission date.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The buyer will check the proposal first that is high on the list. The Featured Proposal allows you to get ahead of the pack by pushing your proposal on top regardless of proposal filters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There will be only three Featured Proposals for every project.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>The Featured Proposal is designed to help freelancers get noticed by buyers. It will put your proposal on top of the proposals when the buyer reviews the proposals from freelancers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Proposals are ranked in a job&rsquo;s proposal list based on their submission date.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The buyer will check the proposal first that is high on the list. The Featured Proposal allows you to get ahead of the pack by pushing your proposal on top regardless of proposal filters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There will be only three Featured Proposals for every project.<\\/p>"}', 16, 0, 2, NULL, 'featured-proposal', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:00:50', '2018-06-08 02:06:42', NULL),
	(90, '{"en":"Change Proposal Terms","ch":"Change Proposal Terms"}', '{"en":"<p>You can propose different terms (such as budget, hourly rate, timeline, etc.) until the buyer hires or rejects your proposal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the relevant proposal on the Active tab. Click the Revise Terms button on the right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter the new terms you want to propose<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can propose different terms (such as budget, hourly rate, timeline, etc.) until the buyer hires or rejects your proposal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the relevant proposal on the Active tab. Click the Revise Terms button on the right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Enter the new terms you want to propose<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 3, NULL, 'change-proposal-terms', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:01:25', '2018-06-08 02:06:50', NULL),
	(91, '{"en":"Interview a Buyer","ch":"Interview a Buyer"}', '{"en":"<h4>Invitations to Interview<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may receive invitations to interview for projects. A buyer can send a message to invite you to an interview asking you to discuss their job. Please respond to the invitations as soon as possible since it will affect your reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can accept or decline the invitations to interview.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To respond to an invitation:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In the Invitations to Interview section, click the job&rsquo;s title.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Accept or decline the invitation.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Active Candidacies<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your active proposals that a buyer responds to and the proposals that are created by accepting invitations will be Active Candidacies. A Message Room will be created for an active candidacy so that you can discuss with the buyer. You can share your contact information and communicate with the buyer at this point. We suggest you use the iJobDesk Message Room, which will be integrated with the contract and accessible later on. Please learn more about the buyer and project in more detail before determining if you want to pursue a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To send a message on an Active Candidacy:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In the Active Candidacies section, click the job&rsquo;s title.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Send Message button to send messages to your buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Write your message to the buyer and click the Send button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<h4>Invitations to Interview<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may receive invitations to interview for projects. A buyer can send a message to invite you to an interview asking you to discuss their job. Please respond to the invitations as soon as possible since it will affect your reputation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can accept or decline the invitations to interview.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To respond to an invitation:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In the Invitations to Interview section, click the job&rsquo;s title.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Accept or decline the invitation.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Active Candidacies<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your active proposals that a buyer responds to and the proposals that are created by accepting invitations will be Active Candidacies. A Message Room will be created for an active candidacy so that you can discuss with the buyer. You can share your contact information and communicate with the buyer at this point. We suggest you use the iJobDesk Message Room, which will be integrated with the contract and accessible later on. Please learn more about the buyer and project in more detail before determining if you want to pursue a contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To send a message on an Active Candidacy:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In the Active Candidacies section, click the job&rsquo;s title.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Send Message button to send messages to your buyer.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Write your message to the buyer and click the Send button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 4, NULL, 'interview-a-buyer', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:01:57', '2018-06-08 02:06:58', NULL),
	(92, '{"en":"How to Use Connects","ch":"How to Use Connects"}', '{"en":"<p>You need connects to submit proposals for jobs. Required Connects are different, depending on factors such as the size and type of project. When a project is canceled without forming a contract with any freelancer, the Connects used on that proposal will be returned for you to reuse. You don&rsquo;t need to use any Connects in case a buyer invites you to a job.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To check your current connects balance:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Your Available Connects balance is shown at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>How many Connects do I need to submit a proposal?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the job you are going to send a proposal.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Required Connects is shown at the top right under the Submit a Proposal and Save buttons.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You need connects to submit proposals for jobs. Required Connects are different, depending on factors such as the size and type of project. When a project is canceled without forming a contract with any freelancer, the Connects used on that proposal will be returned for you to reuse. You don&rsquo;t need to use any Connects in case a buyer invites you to a job.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To check your current connects balance:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Your Available Connects balance is shown at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>How many Connects do I need to submit a proposal?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the job you are going to send a proposal.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Required Connects is shown at the top right under the Submit a Proposal and Save buttons.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 5, NULL, 'how-to-use-connects', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:03:19', '2018-06-08 02:07:07', NULL),
	(93, '{"en":"Withdraw a Proposal","ch":"Withdraw a Proposal"}', '{"en":"<p>You can withdraw your proposals anytime until you are offered a contract. In case you&rsquo;ve received an offer or started a contract, you have to decline or end the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may withdraw your proposal if it is a project you don&rsquo;t want.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw a proposal:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the proposal you are going to withdraw and click the proposal link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Withdraw Proposal button at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select a Reason and submit.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can withdraw your proposals anytime until you are offered a contract. In case you&rsquo;ve received an offer or started a contract, you have to decline or end the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may withdraw your proposal if it is a project you don&rsquo;t want.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw a proposal:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Find Jobs &gt; My Proposals.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the proposal you are going to withdraw and click the proposal link.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Withdraw Proposal button at the top right.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select a Reason and submit.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 16, 0, 6, NULL, 'withdraw-a-proposal', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:03:47', '2018-06-08 02:07:15', NULL),
	(94, '{"en":"Supported Attachment File Types","ch":"Supported Attachment File Types"}', '{"en":"<p>Most file types are accepted, including .zip, .doc, .docx, .pdf, .txt, etc.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Most file types are accepted, including .zip, .doc, .docx, .pdf, .txt, etc.<\\/p>"}', 17, 0, 0, NULL, 'supported-attachment-file-types', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:05:18', '2018-06-08 02:05:18', NULL),
	(95, '{"en":"Use Messages","ch":"Use Messages"}', '{"en":"<p>You can use Messages to communicate and collaborate with the buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A message room will be created when you chat with the buyer, and all your messages will be saved in the room. You will be notified by email when you receive a message from a buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To send a message:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Messages menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find a person you want to communicate and click the person on the left<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type message in the box and click Send button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can use Messages to communicate and collaborate with the buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A message room will be created when you chat with the buyer, and all your messages will be saved in the room. You will be notified by email when you receive a message from a buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To send a message:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Messages menu.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find a person you want to communicate and click the person on the left<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type message in the box and click Send button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 17, 0, 1, NULL, 'use-messages', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:06:04', '2018-06-08 02:06:04', NULL),
	(96, '{"en":"Contract Weekly Limit","ch":"Contract Weekly Limit"}', '{"en":"<p>When you work in an hourly contract, the buyer will set a weekly limit. It is the maximum number of hours you can bill to an hourly contract in one week. The buyer will manage projects by changing the weekly limits, which is a simple tool to help buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Only hours within a contract&rsquo;s weekly limit are billed, and hours in excess of the limit won&rsquo;t be billed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you need to exceed the weekly limit, please discuss this with your buyer in advance and get approval. The only hours within the weekly limit are valid.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>When you work in an hourly contract, the buyer will set a weekly limit. It is the maximum number of hours you can bill to an hourly contract in one week. The buyer will manage projects by changing the weekly limits, which is a simple tool to help buyers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Only hours within a contract&rsquo;s weekly limit are billed, and hours in excess of the limit won&rsquo;t be billed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you need to exceed the weekly limit, please discuss this with your buyer in advance and get approval. The only hours within the weekly limit are valid.<\\/p>"}', 18, 0, 0, NULL, 'contract-weekly-limit', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:08:14', '2018-06-08 02:08:24', NULL),
	(97, '{"en":"Add Manual Time","ch":"Add Manual Time"}', '{"en":"<p>Manual time is often used for billing for work done offline or that might not be recorded properly by the app such as phone calls, non-electronic research, paper-based work, etc.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can ask the buyer to enable manual time for the hourly contract and add manual time. Please discuss this with the buyer and get approval before adding any manual time.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add manual time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Talk to your buyer if they haven&rsquo;t enabled manual time. They can enable or disable manual time on your contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>If they enable manual time, you&rsquo;ll be able to use the Add manual time button in your Work Diary.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Manual time is often used for billing for work done offline or that might not be recorded properly by the app such as phone calls, non-electronic research, paper-based work, etc.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can ask the buyer to enable manual time for the hourly contract and add manual time. Please discuss this with the buyer and get approval before adding any manual time.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To add manual time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Talk to your buyer if they haven&rsquo;t enabled manual time. They can enable or disable manual time on your contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>If they enable manual time, you&rsquo;ll be able to use the Add manual time button in your Work Diary.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 18, 0, 1, NULL, 'add-manual-time', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:08:54', '2018-06-08 02:08:54', NULL),
	(98, '{"en":"Delete Time","ch":"Delete Time"}', '{"en":"<p>Your work diary shows your activities that are tracked by iJobDesk App automatically on an hourly contract. You can only add, edit, and delete time in the current week&rsquo;s work diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You need to check your work diary regularly and delete activities that are not related to the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To delete time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the block of time you want to delete and click the checkbox below it.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Delete button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Your work diary shows your activities that are tracked by iJobDesk App automatically on an hourly contract. You can only add, edit, and delete time in the current week&rsquo;s work diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You need to check your work diary regularly and delete activities that are not related to the contract.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To delete time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the block of time you want to delete and click the checkbox below it.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Delete button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 18, 0, 2, NULL, 'delete-time', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:09:28', '2018-06-08 02:09:28', NULL),
	(99, '{"en":"Your Work Diary","ch":"Your Work Diary"}', '{"en":"<p>Every hourly contract has its own Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Work Diary is useful to literally show what you are working on during the week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It shows a grid of work-in-progress snapshots in hourly rows, each representing a 10-minute billing segment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can log your time by iJobDesk Desktop App.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To log your time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open the iJobDesk Desktop App and log in with your account credentials.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose a contract, enter a memo, and click Start button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update your work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the memo bar or check the box on the segments to update and press the Edit Memo button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Make the changes you want then press Update.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Only the freelancer can add, edit, and delete time in their Work Diary. You can only edit, delete, add time in the current week&rsquo;s Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The previous work&rsquo;s Work Diary is no longer editable.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The only time within the weekly limit on an hourly contract will be billed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to read your work diary<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you log your time by the iJobDesk Desktop App, it takes a snapshot 6 times per hour (every 10 minutes). It will update your work diary with your hourly activity and work-in-progress snapshots.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The memo bars in the Work Diary are color-coded to indicate the status:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Green - Auto-tracked time by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Yellow - Manual time not captured by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The meter records the total number of mouse clicks, scroll actions, and keystrokes per 10 minutes. It doesn&rsquo;t record what you clicked or typed.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Every hourly contract has its own Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Work Diary is useful to literally show what you are working on during the week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It shows a grid of work-in-progress snapshots in hourly rows, each representing a 10-minute billing segment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can log your time by iJobDesk Desktop App.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To log your time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open the iJobDesk Desktop App and log in with your account credentials.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose a contract, enter a memo, and click Start button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To see your work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To update your work diary:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract in the list and click the Work Diary button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the memo bar or check the box on the segments to update and press the Edit Memo button.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Make the changes you want then press Update.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Only the freelancer can add, edit, and delete time in their Work Diary. You can only edit, delete, add time in the current week&rsquo;s Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The previous work&rsquo;s Work Diary is no longer editable.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The only time within the weekly limit on an hourly contract will be billed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to read your work diary<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you log your time by the iJobDesk Desktop App, it takes a snapshot 6 times per hour (every 10 minutes). It will update your work diary with your hourly activity and work-in-progress snapshots.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The memo bars in the Work Diary are color-coded to indicate the status:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Green - Auto-tracked time by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Yellow - Manual time not captured by the App<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The meter records the total number of mouse clicks, scroll actions, and keystrokes per 10 minutes. It doesn&rsquo;t record what you clicked or typed.<\\/p>"}', 18, 0, 3, NULL, 'your-work-diary', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:10:00', '2018-06-08 02:10:00', NULL),
	(100, '{"en":"Reports","ch":"Reports"}', '{"en":"<p>You can use the reports to audit your overall work on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It gives you information on your earnings, hours and payments.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Overview - Overview of the report for the work you did<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timelogs - Reports all the payments and work that took place during the current week.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timesheet- Provides a detailed report of the work you did<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Transactions - All your transactions<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can use the reports to audit your overall work on iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It gives you information on your earnings, hours and payments.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Overview - Overview of the report for the work you did<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timelogs - Reports all the payments and work that took place during the current week.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Timesheet- Provides a detailed report of the work you did<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Transactions - All your transactions<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 18, 0, 4, NULL, 'reports', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:10:27', '2018-06-08 02:10:27', NULL),
	(101, '{"en":"Submit Deliverables to the Buyer","ch":"Submit Deliverables to the Buyer"}', '{"en":"<p>There are a number of file-sharing options out there, and the buyers you work for may have their own way to do it. If you are not sure how your buyer wants you to deliver your work, please get in touch with them to find out.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can always send your deliverables through the iJobDesk Messages.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>There are a number of file-sharing options out there, and the buyers you work for may have their own way to do it. If you are not sure how your buyer wants you to deliver your work, please get in touch with them to find out.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can always send your deliverables through the iJobDesk Messages.<\\/p>"}', 18, 0, 5, NULL, 'submit-deliverables-to-the-buyer', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:11:11', '2018-06-08 02:11:11', NULL),
	(102, '{"en":"Why was my contract suspended?","ch":"Why was my contract suspended?"}', '{"en":"<p>If there is a problem with your buyer&rsquo;s iJobDesk account, your contracts with them will be suspended and you cannot continue to bill that buyer through iJobDesk until the issue is resolved. There are many possible reasons this could occur, although we cannot share the reasons regarding the buyer&rsquo;s account due to privacy concerns.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case a contract is suspended:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Stop working on the contract immediately.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Get in touch with the buyer as soon as possible to find out when the contract will resume.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Warning:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If your buyer asks you to continue working on the suspended contract and then offers to pay you outside of iJobDesk, you should decline and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">report it<\\/a> to Customer Support. It significantly increases the risk of fraud and is a violation of the iJobDesk Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>If there is a problem with your buyer&rsquo;s iJobDesk account, your contracts with them will be suspended and you cannot continue to bill that buyer through iJobDesk until the issue is resolved. There are many possible reasons this could occur, although we cannot share the reasons regarding the buyer&rsquo;s account due to privacy concerns.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case a contract is suspended:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Stop working on the contract immediately.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Get in touch with the buyer as soon as possible to find out when the contract will resume.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Warning:<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If your buyer asks you to continue working on the suspended contract and then offers to pay you outside of iJobDesk, you should decline and <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/contact\\" target=\\"_blank\\">report it<\\/a> to Customer Support. It significantly increases the risk of fraud and is a violation of the iJobDesk Terms and Conditions.<\\/p>"}', 18, 0, 6, NULL, 'why-was-my-contract-suspended', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:11:35', '2018-06-08 02:11:35', NULL),
	(103, '{"en":"End a Contract","ch":"End a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>Buyers usually end the contract and freelancers wait for it. Buyers will make the final payment on a fixed-price contract and leave feedback for you. However, you can end a contract if you wish.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All iJobDesk users have the freedom to end a contract at any time. But please talk to your buyer first because it is always best if everyone is aware of what&rsquo;s going on.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please note the following before you end a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Your Work Diary for that contract will be locked immediately and you cannot make changes.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Both you and your buyer can leave feedback. The other user can&rsquo;t see the feedback you left them until after they have left feedback for you.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To end a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract you want to end and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End \\/ Cancel Contract in overview tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Buyers usually end the contract and freelancers wait for it. Buyers will make the final payment on a fixed-price contract and leave feedback for you. However, you can end a contract if you wish.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All iJobDesk users have the freedom to end a contract at any time. But please talk to your buyer first because it is always best if everyone is aware of what&rsquo;s going on.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please note the following before you end a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Your Work Diary for that contract will be locked immediately and you cannot make changes.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Both you and your buyer can leave feedback. The other user can&rsquo;t see the feedback you left them until after they have left feedback for you.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To end a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the contract you want to end and click the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click End \\/ Cancel Contract in overview tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 18, 0, 7, NULL, 'end-a-contract', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:12:03', '2018-06-08 02:12:03', NULL),
	(104, '{"en":"Feedback","ch":"Feedback"}', '{"en":"<h4>Give Feedback to Buyers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a contract ends, buyers usually leave you feedback as part of that process. As a freelancer, you also can leave feedback about your experience with the buyer. Both parties can leave feedback for a contract that the payments have been made through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the buyer ended the contract, you&rsquo;ll have 14 days to leave feedback.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The feedback system is double-blind, which means that feedback won&rsquo;t be visible until both parties provide it for each other. In case only one party leaves feedback, it will be posted after the 14-day period has expired.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To leave feedback for a buyer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the contract you are going to leave feedback in Archived tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Leave Feedback button to leave feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Read Feedback from Buyers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Feedback for all projects that you worked and received at least $1 will appear on your freelancer profile for the public to see. It will help establish your reputation in the marketplace.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To read feedback from a Buyer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the contract in Archived Tab and click the title of the contract to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Feedback Tab to read the feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<h4>Give Feedback to Buyers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When a contract ends, buyers usually leave you feedback as part of that process. As a freelancer, you also can leave feedback about your experience with the buyer. Both parties can leave feedback for a contract that the payments have been made through iJobDesk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the buyer ended the contract, you&rsquo;ll have 14 days to leave feedback.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The feedback system is double-blind, which means that feedback won&rsquo;t be visible until both parties provide it for each other. In case only one party leaves feedback, it will be posted after the 14-day period has expired.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To leave feedback for a buyer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the contract you are going to leave feedback in Archived tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Leave Feedback button to leave feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Read Feedback from Buyers<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Feedback for all projects that you worked and received at least $1 will appear on your freelancer profile for the public to see. It will help establish your reputation in the marketplace.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To read feedback from a Buyer:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Locate the contract in Archived Tab and click the title of the contract to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Feedback Tab to read the feedback.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 18, 0, 8, NULL, 'feedback', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:12:30', '2018-06-08 02:12:30', NULL),
	(105, '{"en":"Give a Refund","ch":"Give a Refund"}', '{"en":"<p>You can issue a refund after payment is received. Once you issue a refund, you can&rsquo;t reverse it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot refund an amount that is exceeding the lowest of the following:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Net total transactions on the contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Available balance in your iJobDesk account<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To give a refund:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts. If the contract has ended, select the Archived Tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the correct contract in the list and click its title to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the &ldquo;Give a refund&rdquo; button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to refund hours not yet billed for an hourly contract<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you are going to give your buyer a refund for the hours for the current week in an active contract, you can remove them from your Work Diary.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You can issue a refund after payment is received. Once you issue a refund, you can&rsquo;t reverse it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You cannot refund an amount that is exceeding the lowest of the following:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Net total transactions on the contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Available balance in your iJobDesk account<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To give a refund:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts. If the contract has ended, select the Archived Tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find the correct contract in the list and click its title to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the &ldquo;Give a refund&rdquo; button.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>How to refund hours not yet billed for an hourly contract<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you are going to give your buyer a refund for the hours for the current week in an active contract, you can remove them from your Work Diary.<\\/p>"}', 19, 0, 0, NULL, 'give-a-refund', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:13:24', '2018-06-08 02:13:24', NULL),
	(106, '{"en":"File a dispute for a Contract","ch":"File a dispute for a Contract"}', '{"en":"<p>If a buyer fails to release a milestone payment despite delivery of work, you can file a dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To file a dispute on a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts and locate the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the title of the contract to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click File a Dispute link in overview tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Give details to support your claim that the work is complete and payment due. Explain the situation so the dispute specialist understands your claim.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The agent will open a case with a dispute specialist to review your situation.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves. If it is solved smoothly themselves, iJobDesk takes no action and the contract will be restarted.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the buyer rejects the dispute, it enters arbitration. If your buyer fails to respond to your dispute within seven days, it will automatically be resolved in your favor and all funds will be released to you.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Both parties are required to add detailed information about the dispute, which the iJobDesk Dispute Specialist reviews and evaluates them. iJobDesk will carefully consider any information presented. When a dispute is awarded in your favor, we credit the funds to your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>If a buyer fails to release a milestone payment despite delivery of work, you can file a dispute.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To file a dispute on a contract:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to Workroom &gt; My Contracts and locate the contract.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the title of the contract to get to the details page.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click File a Dispute link in overview tab.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Give details to support your claim that the work is complete and payment due. Explain the situation so the dispute specialist understands your claim.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The agent will open a case with a dispute specialist to review your situation.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We encourage both parties to solve the problems themselves. If it is solved smoothly themselves, iJobDesk takes no action and the contract will be restarted.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the buyer rejects the dispute, it enters arbitration. If your buyer fails to respond to your dispute within seven days, it will automatically be resolved in your favor and all funds will be released to you.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Both parties are required to add detailed information about the dispute, which the iJobDesk Dispute Specialist reviews and evaluates them. iJobDesk will carefully consider any information presented. When a dispute is awarded in your favor, we credit the funds to your iJobDesk account.<\\/p>"}', 19, 0, 1, NULL, 'file-a-dispute-for-a-contract', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:13:51', '2018-06-08 02:13:51', NULL),
	(107, '{"en":"Weekly Billing Cycle","ch":"Weekly Billing Cycle"}', '{"en":"<p>Freelancer&rsquo;s billing period for hourly contracts begins Monday at 00:00 midnight UTC and ends Sunday at 23:59 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On Monday at 00:00 UTC following the close of the billing period, buyers are automatically invoiced for hourly contracts.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Freelancer&rsquo;s billing period for hourly contracts begins Monday at 00:00 midnight UTC and ends Sunday at 23:59 UTC.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On Monday at 00:00 UTC following the close of the billing period, buyers are automatically invoiced for hourly contracts.<\\/p>"}', 20, 0, 1, NULL, 'weekly-billing-cycle', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:16:45', '2018-06-08 02:16:45', NULL),
	(108, '{"en":"Get Paid for Fixed-Price Contracts","ch":"Get Paid for Fixed-Price Contracts"}', '{"en":"<p>Your buyer won&rsquo;t be billed for fixed-price contracts automatically. The buyer makes a deposit into escrow and set up a milestone when a fixed-price contract starts. When you submit the milestone deliverable, the buyer will release the funds in escrow.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>No funds in escrow can be returned to the buyer until the contract is complete and you agree or go through dispute mediation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fixed-price contracts are covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Payment Protection<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When your buyer releases a milestone or final payment on a fixed-price job, it immediately shows as pending on your financial account. They become available after the standard five-day security period.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Your buyer won&rsquo;t be billed for fixed-price contracts automatically. The buyer makes a deposit into escrow and set up a milestone when a fixed-price contract starts. When you submit the milestone deliverable, the buyer will release the funds in escrow.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>No funds in escrow can be returned to the buyer until the contract is complete and you agree or go through dispute mediation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fixed-price contracts are covered by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/ijobdesk-payment-protection\\" target=\\"_blank\\">iJobDesk Payment Protection<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When your buyer releases a milestone or final payment on a fixed-price job, it immediately shows as pending on your financial account. They become available after the standard five-day security period.<\\/p>"}', 20, 0, 2, NULL, 'get-paid-for-fixed-price-contracts', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:17:22', '2018-06-08 02:17:22', NULL),
	(109, '{"en":"Get Paid for Hourly Contracts","ch":"Get Paid for Hourly Contracts"}', '{"en":"<p>For an hourly contract, you can use the iJobDesk Desktop App to log time to your Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your buyers are automatically billed for your hours in your Work Diary according to the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/weekly-billing-cycle\\" target=\\"_blank\\">weekly billing cycle<\\/a>. Once your earnings are available in your balance you can withdraw your funds from your iJobDesk Account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you log time over the weekly limit, it won&rsquo;t be billed to your buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers can issue a bonus payment to you manually at any time while the contract is active. So you can negotiate a bonus payment for that time if your buyer agrees.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>For an hourly contract, you can use the iJobDesk Desktop App to log time to your Work Diary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your buyers are automatically billed for your hours in your Work Diary according to the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/weekly-billing-cycle\\" target=\\"_blank\\">weekly billing cycle<\\/a>. Once your earnings are available in your balance you can withdraw your funds from your iJobDesk Account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In case you log time over the weekly limit, it won&rsquo;t be billed to your buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Buyers can issue a bonus payment to you manually at any time while the contract is active. So you can negotiate a bonus payment for that time if your buyer agrees.<\\/p>"}', 20, 0, 3, NULL, 'get-paid-for-hourly-contracts', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:18:03', '2018-06-08 02:18:03', NULL),
	(110, '{"en":"Withdraw Money","ch":"Withdraw Money"}', '{"en":"<p>You may request to withdraw available funds in your iJobDesk Account immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw available funds:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Withdraw<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Get Paid Now button at the top<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose the amount to withdraw and click the Get Paid Now button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Set Up a Payment Method<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You must set up at least one payment method to withdraw funds from your iJobDesk Account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can choose the best payment method for you to withdraw. Please input accurate entry of your account number(s) and details to withdraw successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Add a Payment Method button<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose a payment method you want to add and enter the info required.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>For security reasons, your new payment method will become active in three days<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can remove the payment method anytime.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You may request to withdraw available funds in your iJobDesk Account immediately.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To withdraw available funds:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Withdraw<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Get Paid Now button at the top<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose the amount to withdraw and click the Get Paid Now button<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Set Up a Payment Method<\\/h4>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You must set up at least one payment method to withdraw funds from your iJobDesk Account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can choose the best payment method for you to withdraw. Please input accurate entry of your account number(s) and details to withdraw successfully.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Go to the Accounts menu &gt; Settings &gt; Payment Methods<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click Add a Payment Method button<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Choose a payment method you want to add and enter the info required.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>For security reasons, your new payment method will become active in three days<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can remove the payment method anytime.<\\/p>"}', 20, 10, 4, 5, 'withdraw-money', 0, 1, '2018-06-08 02:18:41', '2018-06-12 13:48:34', NULL),
	(111, '{"en":"Service Fees","ch":"Service Fees"}', '{"en":"<p>Freelancers are charged a fee for your billings with each buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The iJobDesk Service Fee is 10% for total billings with a buyer. Service fees are the same whether the contracts are hourly or fixed-price. In case you invite a buyer through the Affiliate Program, the service fee applied to all contracts between you and the buyer is 5%.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As a freelancer, you pay the iJobDesk Service Fee on all billings, including hours, milestones, and other payments such as bonuses. It is included in the amounts buyers see on your proposals, contracts, and your profile.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Freelancers are charged a fee for your billings with each buyer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The iJobDesk Service Fee is 10% for total billings with a buyer. Service fees are the same whether the contracts are hourly or fixed-price. In case you invite a buyer through the Affiliate Program, the service fee applied to all contracts between you and the buyer is 5%.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As a freelancer, you pay the iJobDesk Service Fee on all billings, including hours, milestones, and other payments such as bonuses. It is included in the amounts buyers see on your proposals, contracts, and your profile.<\\/p>"}', 21, 0, 0, NULL, 'service-fees', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:20:43', '2018-07-08 03:55:30', NULL),
	(112, '{"en":"PayPal Fees","ch":"PayPal Fees"}', '{"en":"<p>You must use your own registered PayPal account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In most cases, your payment transfers immediately. However, there are occasions when it may take up to 24 hours.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will be charged a small per-transfer fee, and there may be additional costs on PayPal&rsquo;s side.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal changes their minimum and maximum transaction amounts from time to time, and you should check with PayPal for current information.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal&rsquo;s outgoing withdrawal fees vary by method, destination country, and currency choice. PayPal also may charge additional fees based on your location.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>You must use your own registered PayPal account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In most cases, your payment transfers immediately. However, there are occasions when it may take up to 24 hours.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will be charged a small per-transfer fee, and there may be additional costs on PayPal&rsquo;s side.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal changes their minimum and maximum transaction amounts from time to time, and you should check with PayPal for current information.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>PayPal&rsquo;s outgoing withdrawal fees vary by method, destination country, and currency choice. PayPal also may charge additional fees based on your location.<\\/p>"}', 21, 0, 1, NULL, 'paypal-fees', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:21:11', '2018-06-08 02:21:11', NULL),
	(113, '{"en":"Wire Transfer Fees","ch":"Wire Transfer Fees"}', '{"en":"<p>Wire transfers will be processed within one business day, but it may take several days to arrive in your bank account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Bank holidays in China or your country can delay your funds.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>iJobDesk charges a $25 fee for each U.S. dollar wire transfer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Wire transfers to non-U.S. Dollar accounts are subject to fluctuating rates of the foreign exchange market. The exchange rate you will receive will be determined by your bank.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your bank may charge an exchange fee or currency spread in addition to or instead of the basic incoming international wire fee. Please ask your bank about the possible fees.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You must be listed as an account holder or authorized signer on the bank account.<\\/p>","ch":"<p>Wire transfers will be processed within one business day, but it may take several days to arrive in your bank account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Bank holidays in China or your country can delay your funds.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>iJobDesk charges a $25 fee for each U.S. dollar wire transfer.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Wire transfers to non-U.S. Dollar accounts are subject to fluctuating rates of the foreign exchange market. The exchange rate you will receive will be determined by your bank.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your bank may charge an exchange fee or currency spread in addition to or instead of the basic incoming international wire fee. Please ask your bank about the possible fees.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You must be listed as an account holder or authorized signer on the bank account.<\\/p>"}', 21, 0, 2, NULL, 'wire-transfer-fees', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:21:38', '2018-06-08 02:21:38', NULL),
	(114, '{"en":"What is the iJobDesk Desktop Application?","ch":"What is the iJobDesk Desktop Application?"}', '{"en":"<p>The iJobDesk desktop app is designed for collaboration on hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Freelancers can use the iJobDesk Desktop App to log time on hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The desktop application is available for recent versions of Windows, Mac, and Linux.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here come some helpful links:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/downloads\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Download<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/install-ijobdesk-desktop-application\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Installation Guide<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/log-time-with-the-ijobdesk-desktop-application\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Log Time with the iJobDesk Desktop Application<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>The iJobDesk desktop app is designed for collaboration on hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Freelancers can use the iJobDesk Desktop App to log time on hourly contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The desktop application is available for recent versions of Windows, Mac, and Linux.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here come some helpful links:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/downloads\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Download<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/install-ijobdesk-desktop-application\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Installation Guide<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/help\\/article\\/log-time-with-the-ijobdesk-desktop-application\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Log Time with the iJobDesk Desktop Application<\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 15, 0, 0, NULL, 'what-is-the-ijobdesk-desktop-application', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:26:57', '2018-06-08 04:37:43', NULL),
	(115, '{"en":"Install iJobDesk Desktop Application","ch":"Install iJobDesk Desktop Application"}', '{"en":"<p>Please <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/downloads\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Download<\\/a> the latest version for Windows, Mac, or Linux.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Windows:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Run iJobDeskSetup.exe and follow the on-screen instructions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Mac:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open iJobDesk.dmg and drag the iJobDesk desktop app to your applications folder.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Linux:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click <u>here<\\/u> for distribution-specific instructions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>Please <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.ijobdesk.com\\/downloads\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Download<\\/a> the latest version for Windows, Mac, or Linux.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Windows:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Run iJobDeskSetup.exe and follow the on-screen instructions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Mac:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open iJobDesk.dmg and drag the iJobDesk desktop app to your applications folder.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To install on Linux:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click <u>here<\\/u> for distribution-specific instructions.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 15, 0, 1, NULL, 'install-ijobdesk-desktop-application', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:27:28', '2018-06-08 02:27:28', NULL),
	(116, '{"en":"Log Time with the iJobDesk Desktop Application","ch":"Log Time with the iJobDesk Desktop Application"}', '{"en":"<p>You can log time on hourly contracts with the application.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you have logging turned on, the app takes random screen snapshots six times per hour - once per 10 minutes. You may delete snapshots from your Work Diary until the end of the work week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Each time segment can have a memo. Make sure that all your time is accurately described in the memo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To log your time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open the iJobDesk desktop app<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Log into your iJobDesk account<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select the correct contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type the memo about what you are working on<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Start button to turn on logging<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","ch":"<p>You can log time on hourly contracts with the application.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you have logging turned on, the app takes random screen snapshots six times per hour - once per 10 minutes. You may delete snapshots from your Work Diary until the end of the work week.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Each time segment can have a memo. Make sure that all your time is accurately described in the memo.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To log your time:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open the iJobDesk desktop app<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Log into your iJobDesk account<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select the correct contract<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Type the memo about what you are working on<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Click the Start button to turn on logging<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>"}', 15, 0, 2, NULL, 'log-time-with-the-ijobdesk-desktop-application', 1, 1, '2018-06-08 02:27:56', '2018-06-08 02:27:56', NULL);
